title: this is a dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Spread pie filling over top of first mixture.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Spread over top and bake 25 minutes longer at 350°.

title: melt-away cheese rounds
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add cheese, flour, salt and paprika or poppy seed.
Form mixture into a dough.
Let rest in refrigerator for about 2 hours.
Shape dough into small even balls.
Place on ungreased microsafe cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with some paprika or poppy seed, if desired.
Microwave on High power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Let rest for a few minutes.
Microwave again on High power for another 30 to 45 seconds.
Let cookies rest for a few minutes.
Remove carefully.
Serve immediately or store in airtight container until ready to serve.

title: jalapeno pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: kielbasi surprise
directions: Simmer, uncovered, all ingredients together for one hour or longer.
We eat it over bread.

title: banana slush
directions: Boil water and sugar to make syrup.
Cool.
Put bananas and frozen lemonade through blender.
Mix other ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze in 6 (1-quart) containers.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Put in punch bowl with 7-Up and mix until lumps are out.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter a baking dish.
To it add bread crumbs, butter and hot milk.
Cool.
Set oven to 325°.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla to bread and milk.
Stir to blend.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: fritata
directions: Saute squash, onion, green pepper in a small amount of olive oil.
Prepare Stove Top dressing according to the directions. Combine this with zucchini mixture.
Cool and add beaten eggs (or egg substitute or egg whites).
Add seasonings and grated cheese. Taste along the way!
Spread into pan or dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or so until firm. Allow to cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: low calorie spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in covered jar or container.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons of mix with 1 cup hot water.

title: chocolate fudge squares
directions: Take 2/3 of softened cookie dough and pat into bottom of square brownie pan.
Melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt in double boiler.
Mix and pour over dough. Crumble remaining dough over top.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: ham, cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet; add onion, garlic and carrots.
Saute until onion is lightly browned.
Mix in sugar, vinegar, cabbage and pepper.
Cover and steam for 8 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir in ham.
Mix in cooked noodles. Thoroughly heat.
Makes 4 (2-cup) servings.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Slit potatoes at 1/4-inch intervals, not cutting all the way through.
Put onion slices and seasonings in slits.

Put margarine, about 1 1/2 teaspoons per potato, in alternate slits. Top with sliced mushrooms. Wrap in foil and grill over hot coals for 55 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle chives on each potato before serving. Serves 8.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with 1 cup pineapple juice (add water, if needed, to make cup) until bubbles.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and oranges. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: happy home recipe
directions: Sift all ingredients together thoroughly in a bowl of loyalty. Stir in equal parts of work and play. Add 1 cup faith, one of hope and one of charity. Add a spoonful each of happiness and song. Season to taste with culture and generous amount of worship.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: guess what? hot dish
directions: Pat uncooked beef into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare dressing as directed on package.
Add celery and onion, if desired.
Put dressing over meat.
Pour soup over dressing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn off oven and let stand 15 minutes.
Slice into squares and serve with cranberry sauce or cranberry jelly.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and pineapple.
In saucepan, bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add 2 cups buttermilk and refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix raw ground beef with vegetables, eggs and seasoned salt. Put teaspoon of mixture on corner of wrapper.
Fold wrapper according to package directions.
Fry in hot oil, turning until all sides are golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
In a large bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add corn syrup, vanilla, whole eggs and egg whites; mix until well blended.
Combine cocoa, flour and salt and slowly add to batter.
Fold in nuts and pour into baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 30 brownies.

title: swedish meatballs #2
directions: Mix together and make meatballs about 1-inch in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put in sauce and simmer 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and chop apples. Place the chopped apples in 12 x 8 x 12 baking dish. Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut egg into the flour until it resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle over the apples. Pour butter over the flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruited ham and pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles about 10 minutes in boiling water.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
In bowl, place ham, fruit and nuts.
Add noodles and mayonnaise.
Toss carefully.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Dip chicken breasts in egg batter, then in flour, garlic and paprika mixture.
Brown chicken in margarine, then add water, bouillon and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy four ways(serves three)
directions: Place cooked spaghetti on a plate.
Pour heated chili on top. Grate cheese on top.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.

title: turkey or chicken barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer to combine flavor throughout. This works great for leftover turkey!

title: southern pie(imagine a "southern style" pecan pie with pecans!)
directions: Combine cereal and water; let stand until water is absorbed. Meanwhile, blend eggs with sugar; add syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Fold in softened cereal.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is puffed completely across top.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: choucroute garni
directions: In skillet cook bacon, onion and garlic until tender.
Drain. Stir in wine, sugar, caraway seed, pepper and cloves.
Add sauerkraut and potatoes.
Top with sausage.
Bring to a boil, reduce, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add apple wedges and cook about 8 minutes until apples are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender; remove from broth and let cool.
Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cut in small pieces. Drain mixed vegetables and mix with chicken and condensed soup and can of broth in casserole dish with rice.
Cover with pie crust and bake at 350° in oven for at least an hour or until brown.
Remove from oven and it's ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Add bran; mix well. Combine water and bananas.
Add alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in
a greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix above and beat well.
Add 3 cups fresh, peeled apples, diced (Rome apples are good).
Add 1 cup chopped walnuts or pecans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour in bundt pan.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook corkscrew pasta according to package directions.
Drain. Cover and set aside.

title: health banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding per directions and then add Cool Whip.
Layer your bowl with wafers, then bananas and then pudding mixture and repeat.
Very low in calories and people love it!
Especially when they find out it is fewer calories!

title: granny's chocolate pie
directions: Heat
milk
in	double boiler.	Add sugar, flour, cocoa and salt
(well
blended),
stirring
until thick and smooth, about 20	minutes.
Beat egg yolks and pour a small amount of hot mixture
into
the	eggs
and
stir.
Then pour back into mixture in	double	boiler	for 5 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: italian gnocchi
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water, salted.
Drain and mash.
Add flour until thick dough forms.
Add salt.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
On floured surface, roll out 1 part at a time, into cylinders 1/2-inch in diameter.
Cut into 1/2-inch long pieces. Flour tines of fork and slightly flatten each gnocchi.
Place on lightly floured towel until ready to cook.
Handle remaining dough in same manner.
Add more flour if dough becomes sticky.

title: church supper dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water; chill until thickened.
Combine marshmallows and milk in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until marshmallows are melted; cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and apples.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Add eggs, flour and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning, tomato sauce, tomatoes and soup.
Arrange chips in shallow baking dish. Spoon meat mixture over chips and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve with apple wedges.

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in pie plate.
Heat in 325° oven for about 15 minutes.
Serve as dip or spread.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 1/2 cup.
Combine juice with eggs, sugar, salt and lemon juice in medium saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add pineapple, celery, apples and walnuts; toss well.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon mixture into 8-inch square pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line bottom of cake pan with cookie dough to form crust.
Bake according to directions.
Mix cream cheese with a little sugar and vanilla until thinned.
Spread over cooled crust.
Layer pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Mix strawberries and glaze. Spread on top.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Saute onion in bacon fat.
Remove from heat; add bread crumbs, milk, salt, chicken broth and broccoli.
Mix well.
Beat 2 egg yolks until creamy and thick; combine with broccoli mixture.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff, but not dry; fold in.
Pour into greased 1 quart casserole dish.
Set in hot water and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine beans and chili powder; mix well.
Combine avocados, salad dressing, bacon, onion and seasonings; mix well.
Layer bean mixture, avocado mixture, olives, tomato, chilies and cheese in shallow bowl.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 6 cups.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine.
Blend in 10x sugar; blend in flour. Press on pizza pan with hands.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: perfect potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, fry the bacon until crisp. Remove bacon from pan, crumble and set aside.
Add onion to bacon fat and saute until browned, about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and water.
Cover pan with lid and cook for 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in salt, soup and milk.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Ladle into bowls and top each bowl with 1/4 cup shredded cheese and some of the crumbled bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pecan fudge
directions: Put sugar in heavy saucepan.
Add cocoa, then milk.
Add Karo and stir well.
Scrape sugar from sides of saucepan and put over medium heat.
Bring to boil, then switch to low heat.
Do not stir.
Boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Drop in butter and sprinkle in a little salt.
Do not stir. Set in container of cold water for 15 or 20 minutes.
Beat until very thick.
Add nut meats.
Beat until almost ready to harden. Pour into buttered platter.
Cut into squares and store in tin box.
Do not make in damp weather.

title: cherry bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salsa
directions: Chop green onions and stewed tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
If canning, bring to a simmer, otherwise, enjoy as is.
Makes 1 gallon of salsa.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peach crisp
directions: Put peaches sprinkled with the brown sugar in 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch square glass pan and cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Make crust from Bisquick, sugar, butter and nuts.
(I use pecans).
Mix this all in a bowl and after removing peaches from oven, sprinkle over the peaches to cover.
Bake at 350° until crust starts to brown, about 30 minutes.

title: country fried steaks
directions: Flour, salt and pepper steaks.
Brown in skillet on both sides.
Place steaks in Pyrex dish.
Place sliced onion over steaks.
Pour soup over onions.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: Blend ingredients.
Grease skillet lightly, then dampen 1/2 slice of bread on both sides, in the liquid.
Fry to light brown on each side.
Serve hot with your favorite syrup.

title: lemon herb marinated chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and put in Ziploc bag. Add chicken and let stand at room temperature 20 to 30 minutes, turning once.
Broil or grill until thoroughly cooked, turning once.

title: fresh fried corn
directions: Heat bacon drippings in large heavy skillet.
Add corn, water and margarine to hot fat.
Add salt and milk mixed with flour; cover and cook for at least 1 hour over very low heat.
Stir from time to time; add margarine.

title: whole wheat waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions. Sift flours, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Combine egg yolks, milk and oil.
Pour into flour mixture and beat just until smooth.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and fold into batter.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Heat cream in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Whisk in egg yolks, one at a time.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats the back of a spoon.
Do not let boil.
Remove from heat.
Whisk in sugar substitute, cocoa powder, chocolate syrup and vanilla extract.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour custard into an ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturers instructions.

title: sugar-free orange applesauce tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine applesauce and baking soda.
Stir in orange juice and zest, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, raisins and melted margarine.
Blend well. Spread the batter in a 9 1/2 x 5-inch loaf pan, lightly sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake 40 minutes to golden brown.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Transfer to wire rack to cool.
Slice 1/2-inch slices. To store, wrap slices individually and freeze.
Makes 18 servings. Exchange:
Bread/starch.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix ingredients; shake on meats, vegetables, casseroles and other foods.
Good seasoning without salt.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, according to directions on package.
When done remove from oven; punch holes in cake with ice pick.
Mix condensed milk, cream of coconut and flavoring.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool completely.

title: quick and easy peach crisp
directions: Drain and slice peaches and place in a square 8 x 8-inch or 6 x 10-inch oblong baking dish.
Combine oats, sugar, flour and cinnamon in small mixing bowl.
Add oil and mix.
Spread evenly over peaches.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Combine 1/4 cup soup mixture, ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt and black pepper in bowl; mixing well.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown in skillet, drain.
Add remaining soup mixture, 1/2 cup water and parsley, stirring well.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, butter, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Roll balls in sugar and place in cookie sheet.
Press down with the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and cook until brown.
Drain on paper towel and roll in powdered sugar.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar and cream.
Boil until comes to soft ball when tested in cold water.
Take from fire and add 1 tablespoon of butter and beat until cool.
Pour in buttered pan.
When hard enough, cut in pieces.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Italian seasoning. Spread in bottom of a baking dish. Cover with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan. (Save a little of each to garnish the top). Pour pizza sauce over the cheese mixture. Garnish with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbling. Serve warm with toasted French bread or pita chips.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Measure sugar, salt and syrup.
Microwave 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and microwave 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Microwave 1 to 2 minutes or until starts to turn golden.
Add baking soda.
Stir and quickly pour out on buttered foil-lined pan.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix with other ingredients.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dutch funnel cakes
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl. Allow to set for 10 minutes.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; spread about 2 tablespoons on cut side of each muffin.
Cut each half into 4 pieces and place on baking sheets; freeze at least 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy venison sausage
directions: Mix the venison and the pork sausage.
Make into patties and fry.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup, dash of Worcestershire sauce and bit of onion.
Put in baking dish.
Drain beans and add.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: easy omelet
directions: Brown onions, peppers and meat in pan with margarine.
Do not use margarine when you use sausage.
(Cook bacon; separate and drain if using bacon.)
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Add Bisquick. Beat.
Add milk and spices.
Pour browned ingredients into 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Center should be set.

title: sesame soy chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl and stir well.
Set aside.

title: beet pickles
directions: Heat mixture to boiling point and pour over hot beets that have been cooked and peeled.
Process in hot water bath for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred and boil cabbage for two minutes.
Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: sunday dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Then add eggs and stir in sugar, cooking oil, salt and flour.
Stir until batter is well mixed.
Let set on countertop overnight, then the next morning, roll out dough on floured board about 1/2-inch thick and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place rolls in greased pan; cover with a clean cloth and let rise while at church or about 3/4 hour.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.
This recipe makes about 18 rolls.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Cube the dry bread.
Place in a buttered 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Pour the milk over the bread. Beat the eggs well. Add the sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and oleo. Blend in the pineapple and pour over the bread.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve hot.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large container.
Store in tightly covered jar.
Use 2 or 3 tablespoons mix to each cup. Fill with boiling water or milk.
Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: scalloped turkey
directions: In a casserole, layer all leftovers (turkey, potatoes, stuffing and gravy) until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blitz torte
directions: Cream shortening.
Beat in sugar and salt.
Then beat in egg yolks, vanilla, milk and flour (sifted with baking powder).
Spread mixture in 2 round greased cake pans.
Beat egg whites until very light.
Add 3/4 cup sugar gradually and spread on unbaked mixture in both pans.
Sprinkle with almonds, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Let cool and put together with Cream Filling.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak in large chunks and flour.
Brown on both sides in skillet, then place in large casserole dish.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper, then add the rest of the ingredients. Add water to make sure enough liquid is in dish.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 275°, checking periodically to make sure casserole does not cook dry.
You can add more water if necessary.

title: packer stew
directions: Put everything raw into roaster.
Cover.
Bake 5 hours at 250°.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate to the 3rd power
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites stiff, gradually adding the sugar and cocoa.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan and cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix whipping cream, milk and pudding mix; whip thoroughly.
Pour over first layer.
Melt chocolate bars in double boiler; add water and spread over other two layers. Refrigerate.

title: fancy green beans
directions: All all ingredients and cook.

title: cool marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours before serving.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, reserving 3 tablespoons liquid. Cook bacon until crisp, drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. Crumble bacon. Cook onion in reserved bacon drippings until tender, but not brown. Add beans, reserved bean liquid, bacon, chili sauce and seasonings. Pour into ungreased 1 quart casserole dish. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, combine baking mix, milk and cheese; mix until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
On ungreased baking sheet, drop dough by spoonfuls. Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix margarine and garlic powder.
Before removing from baking sheet, brush warm biscuits with margarine mixture.
Serve warm.

title: horn yeast rolls
directions: Beat eggs, salt, sugar and margarine.
Add water and then yeast.
Gradually add flour.

title: calas (little doughnuts)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by small teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown; drain on paper towel.
Roll in powdered sugar or cinnamon and sugar.
Batter may be made the night before and stored in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and pumpkin pie spice in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Melt the oleo and dribble over the cake mixture. Sprinkle nuts on top of cake.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: marbled cheesecake with raspberry sauce
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, cream and vanilla in small bowl until smooth.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Remove 1 cup batter; mix with cocoa.
Spoon half the chocolate batter into pie crust.
Evenly pour white batter over chocolate batter.
Top with spoonfuls of remaining chocolate batter.
Cut through batter with knife to create marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serve with raspberry sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine everything, except oats and peanut butter.
Cook over high flame until boiling, then turn down and boil for 3 minutes. Stir in oats and peanut butter.
Drop on cookie sheet or wax paper.

title: mud pie
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies in bottom of a pie plate for crust.
Add enough soft chocolate ice cream for center filling.
Top with chocolate syrup and place in freezer for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet.
Chop onion and add to meat. Cook until tender.
Add soup, tomatoes, mushrooms, taco seasoning, corn and peas.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Line pan with taco chips.
Pour meat sauce over them and place grated cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts at 350°.

title: cherry pineapple dessert
directions: Add dry jello to Dream Whip, then fold all ingredients gently together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: piquant pea soup
directions: In a medium stock pot, saute vegetables in oil.
Add peas, broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 hours until peas are well cooked and soup is a thick puree.
Taste for seasoning, adding salt, if desired.
Serves 4 and freezes well.

title: long lasting slaw
directions: Sprinkle the 3/4 cup sugar over the cabbage and onions, tossing to mix.
In a saucepan, mix the vinegar, salt, sugar (1 tablespoon), celery seed, mustard and turmeric.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add the vegetable oil and pour over the cabbage and onion mixture.
Store in the refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: baked squash and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush apple slices with lemon juice to prevent browning.
Layer squash and apples in a 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with raisins and cinnamon.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: meat marinade
directions: Should make enough marinade for 4 to 6 steaks.
Bring all liquid ingredients to a boil. Add salt and sugar a little at a time, making sure it dissolves.
Put in the bay leaves. Simmer and pour hot over steaks.
Refrigerate.
The longer they soak, the better; best results 24 to 48 hours.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer on medium speed. Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and zucchini together first and set aside.
Let it set.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla, then add flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Combine this with the sugar and zucchini and mix well. Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Melt butter on low heat. Add onion and cook until tender. Add flour, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in pepper and set aside. Flake salmon with fork. Add lemon juice, 1/2 cup corn flakes and white sauce.
Stir well. Refrigerate mixture until chilled. Shape into croquettes and roll in remaining corn flakes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cream candy
directions: Cook until it spins a thread from spoon.
Pour 1 cup whipping cream into mixture a little at a time.
Turn heat down.
Boil until it turns brown in pan.
Pour on a marble slab until cool and then pull mixture.

title: no-fuss rolls
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 425° until done.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Place water chestnuts in shallow bowl and cover with soy sauce.
Marinate for 2 to 24 hours.
Roll chestnuts in sugar and wrap with bacon securing with toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet that has been lined with foil.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Place on micro-safe platter.
When ready to serve, reheat in microwave until hot.

title: coconut dream bars
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and oleo until particles are fine.
Use low speed on mixer.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add oil, beating well. Add eggs, beating well after each one. Add buttermilk and vanilla. Mix well. Stir in fig preserves and pecans. Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients in top of double boiler; cook, stirring occasionally until mixture is blended and hot.
Serve hot in chafing dish with chips or crackers.
Quick and easy.

title: sharon's peanut butter pie
directions: Spoon 1/2 cup fudge sauce into bottom of graham cracker pie crust. Gently spread 1/2 of the container whipped topping over fudge sauce. Place in freezer 10 minutes. Pour milk into large bowl. Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until smooth. (Mixture will be thick.) Immediately stir in remaining whipped topping. Spoon over layers in pie crust. Refrigerate for 3 hours or until set. Drizzle remaining fudge topping over and serve.

title: batter for chicken or shrimp
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Add milk; mix well.
Dip in flour, then batter, then flour.
Fry in deep fat.
Batter is for chicken or shrimp.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cut up fresh fruit and put into mixing bowl.
Add marshmallows and whipped cream to desire.
Put in dessert dishes and top with maraschino cherry.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drai and place in bottom of greased casserole.
Mix soup with about 1/4 cup water and stir in a pan on stove until heated and pourable.
Pour over hamburger evenly.
Spread or sprinkle 3/4 of cheese over soup.
Put Tater Tots over cheese.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until potatoes brown.
Remove about 10 minutes before done and sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Return to oven and let cheese melt.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix well together eggs, sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thickened, about fifteen minutes.
Pour over cubed potatoes and sprinkle on celery seed.

title: date balls
directions: Put dates in food processor; grind until fine.
Mix in coconut.
Make balls.
Top each one with a nut.
Enjoy.

title: chupe de camarones(peruvian shrimp chowder)
directions: Put enough oil to cover bottom of pot.
When good and hot, put tomato, cut into small slices to brown; when well browned, put the finely chopped onion to fry, together with the ground chili, the ground garlic, salt, pepper and marjoram.
When all this is fried, add the well washed shrimp, 2 yellow potatoes (finely cut up), peas, the portions of corn and the well washed rice.
Allow to cook over a slow fire until the peas and rice are almost done, then add the rest of the yellow potatoes, cut in two.
When all this is cooked, add the eggs without beating them.
The moment they fall into the pot, stir from one side with a spoon so the contents coagulate in large pieces.
Add the dried chili, seeded, browned and cut into strips, the milk and the parsley.
Stir and serve.
Makes enough for 8 persons.

title: holiday treats "rum balls"
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and shape into small balls. Roll in confectioners sugar and cocoa.
Store in an airtight container at least a week before using.

title: cheese bacon crescent squares
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides.
Seal perforations.
Sprinkle cheeses over dough.
Combine egg, onion, milk, olives and mushrooms.
Pour over cheeses.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.
Bake at 375° for 22 to 28 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and cut into squares.

title: winnie smith's date loaf
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder, whiskey and vanilla until thoroughly blended.
Add whole dates, cherries and pecans. Do not cut ingredients.
Line a 14-inch loaf pan with foil.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 250° until brown, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
This makes about a 4 pound loaf cake.

title: lemon bbq chicken
directions: Coat
chicken
pieces with flour, 2 1/2 teaspoons salt, paprika
and
teaspoon
pepper.
Melt
butter
in shallow baking pan in a 400° oven.
Remove baking pan from oven; place floured chicken
skin side up in melted butter, then turn skin side down and
return to oven.
Be sure chicken is in a single layer.
Bake
at
for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and pour lemon sauce over each piece.

title: pickle relish
directions: Wash and cut peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Grind up in a meat grinder.
Mix well after ground up.
Put in a pan or kettle with the salt.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, pour into a colander.
Run water over it to wash off salt.
Put in a kettle (large) and put the spices in.
Mix water, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the mixture and let cook for about 20 minutes. Have 12 pint jars washed and sterilized.
Put into jars and seal.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bacon and cashews. Chill.
Mix in bacon and cashews, just before serving.

title: princess potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add flour and seasoning.
Blend carefully and add milk.
Cook until creamy sauce forms, stirring constantly. Pour over rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a buttered shallow baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes in moderate oven.

title: fresh apple spice cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually while beating eggs well.
Pour oil in a little at a time, beating well.
Add orange juice and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; reserve 1/2 cup.
Blend in pecans, apples and raisins (optional). Add/blend remaining dry ingredients.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in melted chips.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with pecans.

title: holly farms potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into quarters.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together with flour, Parmesan cheese and chicken seasoning. Coat potatoes with mixture and then arrange potatoes in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cheesy oat wafers
directions: Beat together Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, butter and water until well blended.
Add combined flour, oregano, paprika and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, mixing until blended. Shape into 12-inch roll.
Wrap securely.
Refrigerate 4 hours or up to 1 week.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in 400° oven about 10 minutes or until golden.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Makes about 6 dozen wafers.
Store in airtight container.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Mound peaches in unbaked pie crust.
In small bowl, mix sugar, eggs and flour until smooth.
Pour over peaches; dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let sit before serving.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Wash, pare and dice potatoes.
Add 1-inch of boiling water. Add potatoes, celery and carrots; cover tightly and boil for 10 to 15 minutes or until fork-tender; drain.
In another saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add milk all at once.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a full boil. Boil 1 minute.
Add cooked vegetables and heat through.
Salt and pepper.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a bowl.
Add butter; cream well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in coconut. Pour into pie crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: texas red chili
directions: In a Dutch oven or large pot, brown ground beef and onion. Drain off fat; add vinegar and seasonings and stir well.
Add tomato sauce, beans and water.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes. If you prefer thick chili, put 2 tablespoons cooking starch into 1/2 cup water; mix well and stir into chili.
Good served with Longhorn cheese, apple and Pan de Lote.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: In Bundt pan, put layer of butter, layer of biscuits, layer of brown sugar, layer of cinnamon, layer of butter.
Continue for three layers.
Can add nuts on first layer (optional).

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger with salt, pepper and diced onion.
Spread the mushroom soup over hamburger.
Add the green beans and corn. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, boil water, dates, prunes and raisins for 5 minutes. Add margarine to mixture.
Cool. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and walnuts. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: jean's beans
directions: Saute the onion and hamburger in fat and add the remaining ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: With pastry blender, cut all ingredients until dough forms, about 15 minutes.
Then knead for about 5 minutes.
Press into a cookie sheet; cut into square shapes with a knife.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
When done, re-cut.

title: german slaw
directions: Grate cabbage; chop pepper and onion.
Mix together.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed; pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: summer salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Break cream cheese into Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Add juice and pineapple.
Cool.
When set, stir and add whipped cream.
Pour into mold to set.

title: elderberry lemon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan. Blend cream cheese and shortening until creamy. Beat in sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs 1 at a time. Add lemon peel, juice, flour and milk. Fold in berries. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: watercress celery soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Blend at high speed 30 seconds.
Pour soup into medium size saucepan. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until soup is heated through. Garnish with sprigs of watercress, if desired.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.
Your time:
2 minutes. Cooking time:
5 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter, and softened cream cheese; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour gradually, beating well. Add vanilla. Fold in pecans and chocolate chips. Bake at 325 for 20 minutes in a greased and floured bundt or tube pan. After 20 minutes, lower oven to 300 and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: colleen's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender, then add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Yields 3 cups.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix thoroughly with a fork.
Add nuts last.
Roll into small balls.
If desired, cover with melted chocolate.

title: belgium vegetable salad
directions: Heat until hot and let cool.
Pour over drained vegetables.

title: mudd pie
directions: Crush wafers; add butter and mix well.
Press into 9-inch pie pan.
Cover with soft ice cream.
Freeze until ice cream is firm. Top with cold fudge sauce (make it cold by placing in freezer for a few minutes).
Store in freezer for about 10 hours.
Serve on chilled plate with chilled fork.
Top with whipped cream and slivered almonds.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Make a glaze of remaining ingredients except oleo.
Mix and cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes, then add oleo.
Add glaze to cooked carrots and serve.

title: millet burgers
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together
in a bowl.
(Rice flour acts as a
binder.) Form into burgers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes
on
sprayed cookie sheet, turning once.
Makes one dozen.

title: easy fudge
directions: Cook butter, sugar and milk on low flame until it boils. Reduce heat to low boil and cook, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream until blended. If you like, add nuts.
Pour into small square glass dish or casserole and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: For each sandwich, put a spoonful of ice cream between 2 cookies and squeeze.
Place in jelly roll pan and freeze until firm.

title: chinese stewed chicken legs
directions: Place chicken legs into a pot.
Add just enough water to stew them.
Add everything else and cover and stew them until done, about 25 minutes.
Good served with rice and a green vegetable. Save the stock, which will aspic, for other recipes.

title: ham and egg foo yong
directions: In a 1-quart glass measure, mix chicken broth with cornstarch, preserves, soy sauce and vinegar.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring twice, until thickened.
Set aside.

title: christmas anise drops
directions: Generously grease cookie sheets.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Refrigerate until the consistency of egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with clear wrap and chill.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; cool and bone. In baking dish, arrange in layers all the ingredients. Use several layers of each. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornish hens
directions: Wash and pat dry Cornish hens.
Lightly salt them.
Mix together oil with nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon, cardamon, salt and pepper.
Coat the hens and marinate overnight.
Cook covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and cook for another 1/2 hour. Garnish with sliced oranges or pineapple on top.

title: emmie's rocky mt. pie("a quickie")
directions: Mix all ingredients together (mixture will be stiff).
Spread in a greased pie pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.
Good hot or later.

title: kate's shortbread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Sift the flour into separate bowl; stir in (with fork) the cornstarch and salt.
Mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture, about 1 cup dry at a time, until smooth.
Roll into ball, then either roll out, cut with cookie cutter or pat into pan.
Pierce top well with fork.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Take margarine, salt, brown sugar and water and combine in a large skillet and heat on low.
Stir, then boil uncovered for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat; add potatoes and pecans.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes, basting often.

title: chicken marvelous
directions: Mix well.
Place in casserole.
May freeze at this point; cover well. Thaw before cooking.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix and pour into 8 x 8-inch well oiled pan.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes until top is browned.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Mix all this with mixer until slices of oranges are broken up and batter is fluffy.
Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake cake at 350° as directed on box.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: vanilla hazelnut biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; lightly butter and flour large baking sheet.
In medium bowl, beat eggs with a fork until foamy.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add sugar and salt, mixing with a fork until blended.
Set aside.

title: lasagne
directions: Layer sauce, noodles, Ricotta, Mozzarella, sauce, etc. Bake until brown and bubbly.

title: our favorite pineapple dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk over double boiler until thoroughly melted and mixed.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat; add butter and stir until melted.
Let mixture cool until mixture congeals. Add pineapple and whipped topping.
Spread cracker crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (reserve 1/2 of crumbs).
Spread with mixture and remaining crumbs.
Chill for 4 or 5 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in oil, add sliced onion and garlic.
Simmer five minutes.
In separate bowl combine other ingredients.
Add mixture to beef, cook on low 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Sift
together	flour,	salt
and soda; set aside.
Put butter in	large bowl.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts and fruit.	Drop by teaspoons on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate (350°) oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Make a sauce with the cream of mushroom soup, green chilies, onion, chicken and salsa.
Layer in 2-quart baking dish tortillas (may be torn into pieces), sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions and bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour well drained pineapple on top of cake.
Combine cream cheese, pudding and milk and beat until smooth and thick enough to spread.
Spread over top of cooled cake.
Top with whipped cream, coconut, nuts and cherries. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheesy chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken pieces in water for 1 hour with salt, pepper and celery.
Remove chicken from pot and debone.
Return chopped meat to broth.
Add carrots, potatoes, rice and bouillon cubes to pot and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Before serving, add cheese and heat until melted.
As an added touch, add finely chopped onion tops or celery tops.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Melt cheese and add milk.
Melt butter in separate pan.
Alternate ingredients in casserole, broccoli, cheese, butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Make sheet cake according to directions.
Cool.
Cut in 1-inch strips.
Line bottom of trifle bowl with 1/2 of cake.
Soak with 1/2 of kahlua.
Cover with 1 box pudding.
Cover with 1/2 Cool Whip.
Crush 3 candy bars and sprinkle.
Repeat layer. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip fruitcake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a loaf pan that's been greased, lined with wax paper and greased again.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and remove wax paper.

title: egg and bacon bake
directions: In a skillet, fry the bacon; drain, leaving 2 tablespoons of grease in the pan.
Saute the onions in the bacon grease.
Stir in the soup, milk, eggs, cheese and seasonings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix milk and pudding with hand mixer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip (don't use mixer for this).
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers (cover entire bottom).

title: bread dumplings
directions: Fold flour into bread cubes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk; don't make dough too soft. Roll dough into bread loaf; cut in half.
Gently drop in boiling salted water.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until dumplings are done. Drain; cool and thinly slice.

title: chicken pie
directions: Take chicken off bone and cut into small pieces. Mix soup, broth and vegetables together. Pour over chicken in deep baking dish.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook/simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° or until brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
Bring tomato soup and water to a boil.
Pour over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger curry
directions: Mash garlic cloves and brown in little oil.
Brown hamburger with onions, salt and pepper and curry blocks.
After browned, add cream of mushroom with a little water and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Melt margarine and add with all other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: coconut banana pudding(from nigeria)
directions: Open coconuts and reserve milk.
Grate coconut meat.
Beat the eggs and mix with coconut.
Add sugar and the reserved coconut milk.
Peel and mash the bananas.
Mix well with the coconut mixture.
Pour into ungreased pie or casserole dish and bake in 400° oven until set and the top is a crusty golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Top, if desired, with whipped cream.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic and green onion.
Saute until tender.
Add tomato paste and crawfish stock.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cornstarch.
Add paprika, cayenne, pepper, salt, basil, Worcestershire and parsley.
Simmer until ready to serve.
Add crawfish and simmer until heated through.
Serve on a bed of hot rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: *Whatever amount you care to use.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients and place in oblong pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: roman casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In skillet, cook beef with sausage, onion and oregano, stirring frequently to break up beef. When beef is browned, pour off fat.
Add undiluted soups, water and cooked noodles; stir gently until well combined.
Pour into 12-by-8-by-2-inch baking dish.
Cover; bake for 40 minutes or until hot.
Uncover; stir.
Top with cheese; bake until cheese melts. Yield:
8 servings.

title: crawfish dinner(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Mix all ingredients in rice "cooker".

title: scented cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add applesauce and glue. Stir to combine.
Work with hands 2 to 3 minutes until smooth. Divide into 4 portions.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut dough with cookie cutter.
Use a straw or toothpick to make small hole in top of ornament.
Makes 32 (2-inch) ornaments.
Drying time: approximately 2 days.

title: granny's squares
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9x9 square pan. Bake 45 minutes until edges along side of pan are golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water, salt and 1 teaspoon margarine to a boil ina blancher.
Add macaroni and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While macaroni is cooking, melt the 1/4 cup margarine in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish in the microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Add cheese and milk and cook on Medium-high for 2 minutes and stir.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer, until cheese is melted.
Stir well until blended.
Drain macaroni well and add to cheese and mix well.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; stir in melted chocolate.
After cooled at bit, add eggs.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Will freeze.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Pour half the batter in Bundt pan.
Put a layer of cinnamon. Then pour the remaining batter.
Bake at 375°.

title: strawberry rhubarb compote
directions: Combine rhubarb, cinnamon, cloves and water in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover and microwave at High (100%) for 10 to 14 minutes or until rhubarb is tender, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Mash rhubarb slightly; stir in strawberries, fructose and food coloring.
Reduce power to Medium (50%).
Microwave 1 minute or until strawberries are heated.
Makes 6 servings.
Calories 65 per serving, cholesterol 0 and sodium 18.

title: easy chocolate syrup
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Add vanilla.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: puffed wheat balls
directions: Place cereal in a large bowl; set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, bring brown sugar and corn syrup to a boil.
Add butter.

title: icebox ginger muffins
directions: Cream butter or Crisco and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Mix in other ingredients in order given.
Sift the flour with the cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt before adding.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Bake in muffin tins slowly at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Will keep 4 weeks.)

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into cubes.
Brown steak in oil.
Add soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add 1 cup water with 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Add celery, onion and bell pepper.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: raspberry slush
directions: Mix together water, sugar and Jell-O until dissolved.
Then add in lemon juice, pineapple juice and vodka (optional) and freeze. Scoop into cup and add 7-Up or ginger ale before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: coconut meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mixture into yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into cool crust; top with meringue.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: unbaked fruitcake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over low heat; add remaining ingredients;
mix
well.
Line graham cracker
box
with plastic wrap.
Pack cake batter into box and refrigerate until chilled and firm.
Keep refrigerated.
Also freezes well.

title: oklahoma caviar dip
directions: Drain black-eyed peas well.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve with corn chips or Doritos.
Other ingredients can be added to taste, such as black olives, parsley or more jalapeno peppers.

title: pork chops and cornbread
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in soup until tender.
Mix in cornbread (which has been crumbled up) and poultry seasoning. Place all this in a baking dish and place pork chop on top.
Add salt and pepper and bake for 45 minutes at 400°, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients,
then add raisins, coconut and nuts.
Bake in unbaked deep dish
pie
shell,
to
45 minutes. Or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix first three ingredients, then add water.
Cook on stove for a few minutes until it thickens slightly.
Remove from stove. Then, if you desire, you may add a dash of vanilla and teaspoon of butter.
Serve hot over ice cream, banana splits, etc.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in a Dutch oven and add enough water to cover chicken.
Heat to boil and cover and reduce heat. Simmer until tender.
Remove chicken from the bones and dice. Reserve 2 1/3 cups broth; use instead of water in cooking rice. Prepare rice and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet and add sliced mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Place mushrooms and chicken in large bowl.
Stir rice with soup and cream.
Mix well.
Combine with other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes, covered, at 350°.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots and celery until tender. Add peas and cook 8 minutes more.
Drain vegetables and save water.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole.
Add as much of the vegetable water needed to make a creamy consistency.
Crush potato chips and spread over top.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Beat egg whites in small bowl until stiff. Place chocolate chips in blender.
Whirl until broken apart.
Add water.
Whirl until smooth. Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Whirl 1 minute until blended.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
If large, cut in half lengthwise.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pack.
Add 2 sprigs of dill weed and 4 peppercorns to each jar.
Pour vinegar solution over cucumbers to within 1/2 inch of top.
Makes 6 to 7 pints. Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Roll in small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Press in mold.
Serves 150.

title: al johnson's brunswick stew
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil in large pot.
Precook all meats and chop.
Add all other ingredients and cook slowly for at least 2 hours.
Stir frequently.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain off grease. Mix all other ingredients together; add sausage and refrigerate to chill.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use a tube cake pan.
With solid shortening, grease pan.
Then lightly flour the pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 minutes or until cake leaves side on pan.
Be careful not to overbake this cake and dry it out.
Use toothpick test after 35 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix together.
Make into patties and fry in oil or Crisco.

title: hot clam cheese dip
directions: Use double boiler or chafing dish.
Blend all ingredients, except arrowroot, cornstarch and clam juice.
Over low heat, when cheese has melted, blend arrowroot and cornstarch with the clam juice.
Add to the mixture.
Stir and cook until thick.
Serve hot as a dip.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large, glass bowl; set aside.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion and salt.
Drain and add the other ingredients.
Stir and heat well; pour over Doritos-type chips.
Cover with grated Longhorn cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with salad and pinto beans.

title: caramel corn
directions: Stir all ingredients, except popcorn and baking soda, until boiling and 272°.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda.
Stir well. Add to popped popcorn.
Put butter on hands and make into balls. Let cool.

title: foolproof gravy
directions: Blend softened butter and Kitchen Bouquet into flour.
Stir with 2 cups of broth (beef, turkey, etc.) over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 2 cups.

title: bread and butter pickles(freezable)
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and salt in a large bowl.
Heat remaining ingredients over low heat until all sugar is dissolved. Pour sugar mixture over cucumber mixture and let stand (refrigerated) for 24 hours.
These can be frozen until ready to serve!
Makes 2 quarts.

title: apple salad
directions: Toss together the first 6 ingredients.
Place about 1/2 c. portions on lettuce.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Put in 400° oven for 8 minutes; cool.
Layer Cool Whip mix on top of cooled pretzels.
Layer strawberries and Jell-O; refrigerate.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Blend 1 minute or chop in blender.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well with fork.
Do not use mixer.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork in crisscross pattern.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Let set a few minutes to cool and remove.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients.
Cover with 1 pint Hellmann's mayonnaise. Cover and chill overnight, then mix.

title: hush puppies
directions: Monkey Bread is a fantasy beloved by children of all ages.
A molded bread made from biscuits, when baked, can be individually pulled apart in small, little clumps to savor.
This unique Monkey Bread Pot is related to the Viennese "turk's head" mold and gives monkey bread its characteristically capricious appearance.
It is decorative, sturdy and it should be added, remarkably easy to clean.
(You can use a Bundt cake pan or round.)

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use 3 level spoons per cup. Pour boiling water in cup; stir well.

title: crumb pea salad
directions: Combine mayo and dressing thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill about 2 hours or longer.

title: pink salad
directions: Whip together the milk and Cool Whip.
Stir the whipped mixture with all the other ingredients and chill for 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place brown sugar and butter in a Bundt pan and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until butter melts.
Stir with a fork until caramel sauce is formed.
Place pineapple slices on sauce with a cherry in the center of each pineapple slice.
Combine cake mix, eggs and juice together and mix well.
Pour over pineapple slices and microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and invert.

title: indian flatbread
directions: Combine flours with salt.
In a large bowl, mix milk with 3/4 cup of warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon of the butter and gradually begin adding flour.
Blend well to make a soft dough, adding more flour or water as necessary.
The consistency should be a little less firm than loaf-bread dough.
Cover bowl with a lint-free cloth and let the dough "rest" for about an hour.
Then turn it out onto a floured surface and divide into 4 equal parts.

title: fruit cobbler(any fruit)
directions: Line a Dutch oven with foil.
Place a layer of fruit, sugar to taste and 1/2 of cake mix on foil; repeat procedure.
Put coals on top of Dutch oven after placing pot on hot coals.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, 3/4 cup of sugar, salt, eggs, milk, vanilla and 1/3 stick melted margarine.
Blend with mixer until smooth.
Pour in long, greased baking dish.

title: butter icing
directions: In a saucepan, pour 1 cup milk.
Gradually add flour with a fork, stirring quickly to avoid lumps.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly. Set aside to cool.
Cover paste with wax paper to keep smooth.
In a small mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar. Add cooled paste. Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and seasoning in saucepan.
Stir in 3/4 cup of beet liquid and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add beets and butter.
Simmer about 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hot pickles
directions: Drain pickles and place into a large bowl. Pour in hot sauce, sprinkle sugar over pickles and let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Place pickles now into pint jars and seal.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Cool and remove from bone.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook onion and spaghetti in chicken broth until tender.
Drain.
Heat soup and tomatoes in microwave.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Serve.

title: beef rendang
directions: Add meat and continue to fry, but on lower heat.
Add coconut milk, salt and sugar.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until meat is tender.
If meat needs a longer time to cook, and gravy dries, add a little water.
Feeds 4 to 6.

title: witches brew
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cider.
Tie spices in a small cheesecloth.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with a twist of orange peel.

title: stir and drop cookies(no mixer needed!)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs with fork until well blended. Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon.
Slowly blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Slowly add flour to cookie mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet.
If desired, press each cookie flat with bottom of glass dipped in water then sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Sprinkle with red or green sugar crystals at holiday time.
Great for kids to make!

title: orange balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, sugar and nuts together.
Add orange juice and mix by hand.
Melt butter and mix again.
Roll balls in coconut and lay on paper towels, then refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light (don't overbeat).
Add sugar; beat again.
Mix in syrup, margarine, pecans, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until center is set.

title: spam sandwiches
directions: Mix together adding mayonnaise and mustard.

title: got me a husband bread(quick yeast bread)
directions: Combine yeast, water, shortening, salt, sugar and 1 1/2 cup flour in a large mixing bowl. Mix with an electric mixer on low to medium speed until batter is smooth; then stir in remaining flour. Set in a warm place and allow to rise for 30 minutes. Stir down and beat 25 strokes with a wooden spoon. Pour into a large well- buttered loaf pan. Let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 425° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven, butter top and place on rack to cool.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes or yams until done.
Take off skins and slice in half lengthwise.

title: grandpa jim's chicken surprise
directions: Put seasoning packet from stuffing mix in water and heat. Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Place Swiss cheese slices over chicken.
Next spread stuffing mix over chicken and cheese. Pour chicken broth and heated mixture over chicken and cut butter into pats, placing it over the chicken.
Cover with glass lid or tinfoil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix well all ingredients; spray skillet well or use Shedd's Spread and cook at medium-high heat until bubble forms and edges are done.
Turn and cook other side.
Remove from heat.
Makes 4 small pancakes.

title: fireside stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Place all ingredients, except biscuits, into a large casserole dish and blend well.
Cover and bake for 3 to 4 hours at 300°.
When meat is tender, increase heat to 400° and top stew with biscuits.
Bake for 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: grape jam for diabetics
directions: Put in pan and bring just to a boil.
Then put in jars.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Place the candy bar, marshmallows and milk in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth. Cool. Fold in whipped cream; pour into crust. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°F.
Prepare crust;
set aside.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips, stirring constantly.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
add melted chips and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is set.
Cool;
chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; shape into patties.
Brown on all sides in very small amount of oil.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Pour over meatballs and simmer 15 minutes, turning to glaze.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut in small pieces.
Mix with sour cream and soups.
Top with Ritz crackers which have been coarsely broken.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all ingredients.
Form into a loaf pan.

title: old fashion syrup cake(from the 1800's)
directions: Mix sugar, lard and eggs.
Add all other ingredients and bake until done.
Use a broomstraw to test cake.
If it comes out clean when punched into cake, the cake is done.
Makes 3 layers.
Now our time:
bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chef fido's rover's reward dog cookies
directions: In a large bowl, pour hot water over oleo.
Stir in powdered milk, salt and egg.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Knead 3 to 4 minutes more, adding more flour if necessary to make a very stiff dough.
Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with cookie cutters.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Allow to cool; dry out until hard.

title: frango style mints
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add chocolate; blend with beater. Add 1 egg at a time and beat well after each for at least 1 minute.
Add flavoring.
Pour into 12 paper lined cupcakes.
Keep in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, decorate with whipped cream, cherries, slivered almonds or crushed peppermint.

title: one-pan lasagna
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan or buffet electric skillet, layer as follows:
cooked, drained meat, 1 package spaghetti sauce mix, cottage cheese, uncooked lasagna noodles, 1 package spaghetti sauce mix, basil, parsley and salt.
Pour pureed tomatoes, tomato sauce and water over all, making sure all noodles are moistened. If using skillet, bring to a boil, cover and simmer 35 minutes or until noodles are tender.
If using oven method, cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake, following directions on box.
Pour into an oblong baking dish (14 x 9-inch).
Bake according to directions.
When cake is done, but still hot; prick top of cake with a fork.
Pour condensed milk over the top (slowly fill in the holes made with fork).
After the milk has soaked in; spread Cool Whip over the top.
Sprinkle with frozen coconut.
Refrigerate.
Super good and easy.

title: jazzy tea
directions: Mix the water, lemonade and instant tea.
When ready to serve, add Sprite.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup together.
Add chicken and mix.
Turn into casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburg-onion pie
directions: Mix well 1 cup Bisquick and cream; knead 10 times on board lightly dusted with Bisquick.
Roll dough into a circle to fit 9-inch pie pan.
Ease into pan; fork edges.

title: squash-carrot puff
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine ingredients and season to taste.
Spread in a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Top should be golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice onion and green pepper and saute in small amount of oil until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake covered at 350° (325° if using glass pan) for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: quick strawberry cake
directions: Crumble or slice cake in a pan.
Pour instant pudding (prepared as directed on box) over cake.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over pudding.
Keep refrigerated.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh veggies, chips, etc.

title: beef turnovers
directions: Brown meat with gravy mix, bean sprouts, chestnuts and onion in skillet, stirring until beef is crumbly; drain. Separate crescent rolls in triangles.
Cut
triangles into halves. Place 1 spoonful of beef mixture in center of each triangle. Fold over filling; press edges to seal. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 15 minutes. Yields 32 turnovers.

title: squash paddies
directions: Microwave grated squash a little bit before mixing all ingredients. Fry like pancakes.

title: soda bread
directions: Smear 2 tablespoons of the butter evenly in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Line the buttered skillet with a circle of waxed paper. Melt 2 more tablespoons butter and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add currants to dry ingredients.
Toss well.
Whisk together buttermilk, eggs and melted butter.
Add to the dry ingredients.
(Add caraway seed, if desired.)
Mix until just blended.
Spoon batter into the prepared skillet and smooth top.
Dot the top with remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake until golden brown and puffed, about 60 minutes. Cool slightly; remove from skillet and cool completely on a rack.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring to boil water and margarine.
Remove from heat and add flour; mix with wooden spoon.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in with a wooden spoon.
Spread mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread batter on bottom and up the sides of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Using mixer, blend milk, pudding and cream cheese until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with Hershey's syrup.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fry bacon; cook minced onion in grease.
In 2-quart casserole alternate, repeating 3 times, layers of zucchini, cheese, tomatoes, onion and bacon mixture, crackers crumbs and seasoning. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
If necessary, brown under broiler just before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Can also top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup margarine.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cheese ball appetizer
directions: Place half of the chopped nuts (1/2 cup) on a dinner plate and set aside.
Mix the remaining nuts with all other ingredients and form a ball or log.
Coat the outside of the cheese ball by rolling in the reserved nuts.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: hillbilly fruit cake
directions: Dredge cut up fruit with 1/2 cup flour.
Mix cake mix as directed; add extracts.
Beat 2 minutes with beater on medium speed.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat 2 minutes longer.
Spread evenly on 2 wax paper covered and oiled bread pans or in oiled and wax paper covered angel food pan.
Bake 3 to 3 1/2 hours at 275° with a shallow pan of water below the cake.
Cool and glaze with hot white corn syrup.
May be decorated with candied cherries or pineapple.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables on low heat until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Add stock and milk to make a smooth sauce.
Add soda and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add parsley before serving.

title: salsa
directions: Place the chopped green celery and green pepper, diced jalapenos, salt and sugar in the food processor.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium-high heat.
Boil for 4 hours, stirring often.

title: melon-cucumber salad
directions: Mix oil, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper in tightly covered container.
Toss with melon and cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 8 hours.
Drain.
Serve on salad greens.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In skillet, brown the sausage and drain well.
Add all ingredients, except cheese, and add to crock-pot.
Stir well. Cover and cook on low setting for 12 to 14 hours.
Taste for seasoning.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Pasta may be added, if desired.
(Soup does not have to be cooked in crock-pot.)

title: crispy cookies
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add both sugars.
Mix well; add egg, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls (teaspoonful).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, sour cream, oil and eggs for 3 minutes.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over 1/2 of the cake batter.
Dribble remaining batter over this and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured) about 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan yams
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart baking dish.

title: crab-stuffed avocados
directions: Peel avocados and cut in half. Place half a peeled clove of garlic and 1 tablespoon of vinegar in each half.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add well beaten eggs.
Put juice of oranges in measuring cup and add enough water to make 3/4 cup of liquid.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Pour batter into 3 foil bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving size portions.
Dip in seasoned flour and brown in skillet.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cover with onion, then mushrooms.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite sized pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 12 inch pan.

title: zippy pineapple slaw
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: kenny's butter bean pie
directions: Cook butter beans in crock-pot overnight.
Drain and place in large casserole dish.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add Ragu to hamburger; mix well and pour over butter beans.
Slice cheese and layer over top of casserole.
Mix cornbread mix according to directions and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° until cornbread is brown.

title: pot pie
directions: Put egg in a measuring cup and fill up to 1/2 cup with milk. Pour in a mixing bowl.
Add shortening and salt.
Add enough flour to roll out.
Cut in strips as desired.
Put into boiling broth. Cook until tender.
Serves 4.

title: fruit flavored popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in 4-quart bowl that can go in microwave; set aside.
Cook margarine in 1-quart glass bowl 30 to 40 seconds in microwave on High.
Stir in Jell-O and corn syrup.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes or until full boil.
Stir; add baking soda.
Mix well; mixture will foam up.
Pour over popped corn; toss to coat well.
Cook on High (microwave) 4 to 5 minutes. Stir after each minute.
Turn onto wax paper.
Spread out to cool.
Break in small pieces.

title: l.b.j. beans
directions: Brown the ground beef with garlic and onion.
Mix ground beef with remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook a minimum of 2 hours in crock-pot, stirring frequently.
I have cooked as long as 4 hours before serving.

title: garlic bubble bread
directions: Thaw dough.
Blend other ingredients.
Cut walnut-sized pieces of dough.
Dip into butter mixture.
Place in well-greased loaf pan.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Brush with remaining butter mixture.

title: jane's cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange rind.
Mix with sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Mix jello in hot water.
Add cold water and undrained pineapple.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breast in a baking pan that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Pour salsa over chicken; return to oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese; return to oven just until cheese melts.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into ball.
Frost with softened cream cheese with chives.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a bowl, mix peanut butter and sugar together.
Add melted butter, a little at a time, until you can form balls 1/2 the size of a golf ball.

title: shrimp or onion ring batter
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg white, until you get the lumps out.
Beat the egg white until stiff then fold the mixture into the egg. Dip shrimp or onion rings and fry in deep oil.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Blend cold water and cornstarch in pan.
Add boiling water. Cook until mixture becomes clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites (room temperature) until foamy.
Add sugar gradually until stiff.
Add cornstarch mixture; beat well.
Spread over cooled pie filling. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: honey sage whipped butter
directions: In small dish combine sage and honey, mix well. Microwave on high for 15 seconds. Cool 2 minutes. In a small bowl, beat butter at medium speed until fluffy. Add honey mixture, beat well.
