Spoon mixture into crock or serving dish. Cover tightly. Garnish with sage leaf if desired. Store in refrigerator. Makes about 1/2 c.

title: eagle brand pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 15 minutes and reduce to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mini turkey loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine all ingredients.
Press into muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned and no longer pink in centers.
Serve with cranberry sauce, if desired.

title: lamb stew
directions: Place meat in brazier; season with salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Place over high heat and bring to boil.
Stir and boil 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove scum.
With a clean, damp towel, wipe residue from inside of pot.
Simmer 1 hour.
Wash and drain vegetables.
Add boiling water to meat; add vegetables.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch. Serve.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box, using juice from pineapple as part of water.
Melt butter and spread evenly in pan (iron skillet is best).
Sprinkle sugar evenly over oleo.
Arrange pineapple and cherries as desired.
Pour cake mixture over this. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and beefaroni with biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Place	biscuit on top and bake for at least 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan and heat until cheese is melted.
Add chicken and pour in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25-30 minutes.
Serve hot with scoop Fritos.

title: savory ham and kraut puff
directions: For Puff:
Grease a 9-inch pie plate with the butter or margarine.
In a blender container or food processor bowl, place eggs, milk and flour.
Cover; blend 30 seconds.
Pour batter into pie plate.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: quick taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, water and olives.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place these in ungreased 9 or 10-inch pan, pressing to form a crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed corn chips over the bottom of crust.
Spoon meat mixture over crust and corn chips.
Spread sour cream over meat mix and cover with cheese.
Sprinkle on remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until crust is golden brown.
If desired, serve in wedges, topped with shredded lettuce and avocado slices.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice until soft; drain and cool.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool until jelly-like or quivery stage.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill and let set.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients, working with hands.
Roll out dough to 1/4 inch thick and cut into narrow strips or use a cookie press. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut the cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices and place in a 12-inch round pizza pan with pieces touching. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Place spinach in buttered casserole.
Put chicken over spinach and cover with egg slices. Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread over casserole and top with buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and bread cubes are brown.

title: full cream nut caramels
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook sugar, corn syrup and 1 cup of cream about 10 minutes.
Add the other cup of warm cream slowly and cook about 5 minutes.
Have heat only high enough to prevent boiling over.
Add butter, a little at a time.
When thermometer reads about 230°, lower heat and cook to 240° to 244°.
If necessary, to prevent scorching, stir occasionally, toward end of cooking. Remove from heat as soon as temperature is reached.
Add salt and vanilla.
After several minutes, mix gently.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Add nuts gently.
Pour into well-oiled or buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool until solid enough to cut.
Wrap individual pieces to prevent spreading.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed potatoes and sour cream and set aside.
Then spread layer of potato mixture and a layer of cheese.
Repeat.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening until consistency of coarse corn meal.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together.
Mix into shortening mixture.
Knead.
Pinch off balls about size of egg and roll out on a floured board in round shape. Makes about 10 pies.
Sprinkle sugar on pie shapes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread bread with butter.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside.

title: pancake mix recipe
directions: Mix
well
all ingredients.
Store in airtight containers. When ready	to use for each 1 1/2 cups pancake mix use 1 beaten egg,
cup water and 2 tablespoons melted shortening. Mix well and
fry
on
hot
griddle.
We
use milk instead of water, then I omit the 4 cups dry milk.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together and roll
into small balls.
Melt 12 ounce package chocolate chips and 1/2 bar paraffin in double boiler. Dip balls in mixture.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Combine ingredients with a mixer.
Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool for 1 to 2 minutes.
Prick cake to bottom with a knife.
Pour on Lemonade Glaze.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Brown beef in skillet and mix it with the pizza sauce.
Add the biscuits; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 7 or 8 people.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and jello in a bowl.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Bake in layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar; cook 3 minutes.
Add jello (no water) and cream cheese.
Leave on low a while until all big chunks of cheese soften.
Cool after stirring until well mixed. When it starts to thicken, add celery, nuts and apples.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions and fold in.
Chill several hours.
Serves 12.

title: glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 3 minutes.
Beat glaze for a few minutes.
Pour over cake, while cake is slightly warm. This is great for Bundt cakes.
Add rum if you wish.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat in very hot oil, gradually cook flour until dark brown, but not burned, stirring constantly.
Stir in onions, pepper, salt and garlic powder to taste.
Cook until onions and peppers are tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain liquid from oysters into flour mixture.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, okra and water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Add oysters, shrimp, crab and pepper sauce.
Cook until shrimp turns pink and opaque.
Serve in bowls with rice.

title: slaw(slaw is good with any meal.)
directions: Shred cabbage in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 30 seconds in blender on high, or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Then add all other ingredients.
Drain extra juice off the pineapple and strawberries.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in heavy large saucepan; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly and quickly.
Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper.
Cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: english trifle
directions: Split cake into two layers.
Fill with jam.
Cut or break into 12 to 15 pieces.
Place in 2 to 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Sprinkle sherry over cake.
Spread fruit over cake pieces.
Cook pudding as directed on package using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Cool to room temperature, pour pudding over fruit and cake.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Three to four hours before serving, whip cream and sweeten with powdered sugar.
Spread over pudding.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream brown sugar, sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add the remainder of the ingredients and mix well.
Divide dough into 3 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill well.
After about 1 hour, slice the rolls 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tropical storm
directions: Place all ingredients in blender, adding sugar or honey if desired.
Cover; blend until ice is crushed.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: kielbasi baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered and 45 minutes uncovered.

title: tropical spring salsa with pork(low in fat, sugar and carbohydrates)
directions: Mix all ingredients except pork until well blended.
Serve over hot sliced pork.
Makes 12 servings, 3 oz. cooked pork and 2 Tbsp. salsa each.

title: jordan's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, eggs and oil.
Stir just enough to mix ingredients together. Batter may be lumpy.
Shake blueberries in the 1 tablespoon flour and fold into mixture.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin tins. Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30-35 minutes.

title: sky high biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the flours, baking powder, sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Cut in butter until
mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add egg and milk, stirring.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll or pat gently to 1-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 to 2-inch biscuits.
Place in greased 10-inch iron skillet or 9-inch square pan.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork slowly.
Add 1 cup water and bouillon cube.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Then add wet ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or two round pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until top of cake springs back when touched.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: michelle's pineapple-walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients and pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: cookie cake
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients.
Pour over flour mixture of flour, sugar and soda.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in a greased and floured sheet pan at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: steak and onions
directions: Cut up steak in small pieces.
Brown in skillet.
Cut up onion; fry in separate skillet.
When steak is nearly done, add onion, salt, pepper, tomatoes and garlic.
Add water and let simmer.

title: winning apple cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg; mix until well blended.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add oil and 3 eggs.
Mix just until moistened.
Fold in apples and nuts. Reserve 2 cups of batter.
Pour remaining batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over batter. Carefully spoon reserved batter over cream cheese mixture. Spread lightly to cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until wooden pick clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top of cake.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross on each one with fork dipped in water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: pancit canton
directions: Cut chicken breast in small pieces.
Saute the garlic, onion and chicken breast and cook about 3/4 done.
Add 1/4 cup of water, 3 tablespoons of soy sauce, cabbage, carrot and celery.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Place canton noodles in; stir.
Salt and white pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer 3 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix ingredients in a 2 qt pot. Simmer until beef chunks are cooked tender.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with salts and marinate in liquid smoke and Worcestershire overnight.
The next morning, wrap tightly in foil and bake at 300° for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove from oven and cool. Drain off liquid and save.
Place in refrigerator or until well chilled.
Slice 1/4-inch thick across the grain and place in baking dishes.
Remove fat from liquid.
Heat liquid and stir in catsup to taste.
Pour liquid over sliced brisket (may be frozen at this point for later use).
Bake at 275° to 300° for 2 hours. Serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Stew chicken with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
After cooling and boning, cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In a large saucepan, cook green pepper and onion in margarine or butter until tender. Stir in soups, tomatoes and green chilies and cheese.

In 3-quart shallow baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch), arrange alternate layers (3) of tortillas, soup mixture and ending with a topping of cheese. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly and cheese is browned.
Serves 10 to 12 and can be frozen before or after cooking.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add buttermilk and beat well. Combine flour and soda; gradually stir into creamed mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut into rounds with a cookie cutter.
Place 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Boil first 3 ingredients for 1 minute. On cookie sheet, sprinkle almonds; pour butter mix over.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Drain vegetables, chop onion and celery; slice chestnuts and grate cheese.
Combine vegetables, celery, onion and chestnuts. Add cheese and mayonnaise and mix well.
Place mixture in greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and dribble with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fake bread
directions: Knead like bread.
Shape and put on cookie sheet.
Mixture must be baked within 20 minutes or will crack and break.
Bake at 300° until toasty brown.
Can be brushed with egg yolk or glue, then decorated.

title: fluffy cheesecake
directions: Pour milk in deep small bowl. Put bowl and beaters in freezer until ice crystals form on the edge.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Press 3/4 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan firmly.
Set aside.
Beat chilled milk on high speed until it's real fluffy.
In another bowl beat cheese and 1/2 cup sugar until creamy.
In cheese and sugar mixture, blend in jello, vanilla and food coloring.
Lastly, pour milk in mixture.
Beat for 2 minutes at high speed. Pour into pan with crumbs and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Using doughnut cutter, cut ring from each slice of bread; set aside.
Tear remaining bread scraps into pieces; place in greased baking dish. Place cheese slices over bread.
Layer chicken, onion, broccoli and pimento over cheese.
Place bread rings on top.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard; blend well.
Pour egg mixture evenly over casserole; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 325°.
Uncover baking dish; bake at 325° for 55 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 12 servings.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press onto bottom and 2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool on rack while preparing filling.

title: russian potato salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grease pan.
Grease brown paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gelatin banana splits
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and pour in bowl.
Chill until firm.
Cut bananas in half, brush them with lemon juice and arrange them in banana split dish.
Put gelatin on bananas and top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: almost better than sex cake
directions: Fix cake
mix
as directed and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan. Right out
of
oven,
poke
holes
in
cake with end of wooden spoon. Pour
milk	and
topping into holes.
Wait for cake to cool, then spread Cool Whip over top of cake.	Sprinkle candy on top.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
in
a large pan.
(Mix until well
coated.) Place in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done and a little brown on top.

title: quiche with artichoke hearts
directions: Grease quiche pan and put the thawed dough on the bottom (the leftovers you can use for the top).
Spread the breadcrumbs, artichoke (cut in pieces) and half of the amount of cheese in the pan.
Put in a bowl the cream, eggs, cheese, pepper and salt; stir and pour in the pan.
If you have leftover dough you can make a figure out of it (with a cookie cutter) and decorate the pie.
Put in a 200° C (400°F.) oven for about 40 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: In large skillet, brown in hot oil until golden on both sides. Yields 4 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan, layer pineapple evenly. Next, put pie filling on top of pineapple.
Put dry cake mix on top of these and smooth until flat.
Pour chopped nuts on top, then margarine or butter cut in pieces.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon, in a large, shallow baking dish.
Mix well.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Add everything in pan and boil until thick about 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil and cool.
When cool, add rest of the ingredients.
Mix and store in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Serves

title: chocolate shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stir flour, sugar and cocoa in a bowl to mix.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until coarse crumbs form. Put crumbs on middle of ungreased cookie sheet.
Press into an even round, 8-inches in diameter.
Lightly score with a blunt knife in 12 wedges.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until shortbread looks dry.
Remove sheet to wire rack.
Cut wedges all the way through. Cool and dust with confectioners sugar before removing from sheet.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cream peanut butter until it is smooth.
Add 1 tablespoon of milk; mix well.
Add raisins; mix well.
Break up graham cracker and mix with other ingredients.
Add other tablespoon milk; add sweetener and vanilla; mix well.
Form into ball or make into bar shaped piece.

title: triple cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Stir refried beans and sour cream together.
Spread a spoonful of bean mixture across the center of a tortilla.
Sprinkle ground beef and cheese over bean mixture.
Fold tortilla to make an enchilada and place in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Repeat with remaining tortillas.
Spread the enchilada sauce over the tortillas, covering completely.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups, sour cream and 1/2 of cheese together.
Spoon over hash browns.
Put rest of cheese on top, then crush Ritz crackers and put on top. Put butter on top of crackers.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: spicy pineapple and zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer to blend.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla and continue beating until foamy.
With a spoon, stir in zucchini and drained pineapple.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add raisins and chopped nuts. Stir carefully into first mixture until well blended.
Grease and flour two 5 x 9-inch loaf pans and divide batter between them. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans 15 minutes and turn onto racks to cool.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: In large bowl, blend cake mix with pudding, water, eggs, and oil.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in the center.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove to rack to complete cooling.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, egg, shortening and water; beat until smooth.
Spread in a deep dish pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spoon carefully in prepared pie plate. Do not mix.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until crust is golden brown.

title: pineapple coconut inside-out cake(lo-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix, 1 package pudding mix, Egg Beaters, water and oil in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed 1 minute or until blended.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes. Stir in 1 1/3 cups of the coconut.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in unbaked pie shell. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rhubarb.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Then add evaporated milk and homogenized milk.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth. Add vanilla.
Pour over vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put the spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Drop bag of spices into cider mixture. Slowly bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: potato cheese souffle
directions: Preheat
oven	to

potatoes

until smooth.
Add milk, salt, pepper, butter and onion;	beat until fluffy.
Stir
in

cheese and add beaten egg yolks.
Beat the egg

until they stand in soft peaks and carefully fold into potato mixture.
Turn into an ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole and
bake for 1 hour, until well-puffed and firm in center. Serve at once.
Serves 9.

title: apple casserole
directions: Slice apples and place in greased baking dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Crumble biscuits, combine with brown sugar and cracker crumbs.
Spread evenly over apples.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In medium-size glass bowl, combine cauliflower, tomatoes, pepper slices and olives.
In screw-top jar with tight-fitting lid, combine oil, vinegar, mustard, garlic, salt, basil and ground pepper.
Cover tightly and shake until well combined.
Pour over vegetables, cover tightly, and refrigerate overnight.

title: three layer salad
directions: Prepare lime jello and pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients, except cherry jello. When cool, pour mixture on top of lime jello and chill until firm. Mix cherry jello and pour on top.
Chill until firm.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.

Place chicken chunks in bottom of casserole dish. In a bowl, mix together soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Add spices to mixture. Sprinkle garlic and chili powder on top of chicken and sprinkle a few tortilla chips on top of chicken.
Pour soup mixture on chips. Add Velveeta and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven and add remaining chips to cover cheese. Bake an additional 15 minutes until chips darken.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine pineapple and coconut in mixing bowl, add the eggs and sugar and mix well.
Sift the flour, measure and then sift again with the salt and baking soda.
Add this to the first mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 3 greased 5x9 loaf pans.
Bake in a moderately slow oven, 325° for one hour.
Remove and turn out onto wire racks to cool.
Delicious sliced thin and spread with cream cheese!

title: honey sugar cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, sugar, honey, egg and vanilla until thoroughly blended. Blend in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cover. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water; mash. Add margarine, sour cream and cream cheese. Put in baking dish sprayed with Pam. Add shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until brown and cheese melts, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Sift cocoa with flour.
Add slowly to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix cheeses, parsley flakes and eggs in separate bowl. Do not cook noodles.
Place a layer of sauce mix in baking dish, then a layer of dry noodles, then layer of cheese mixture. Continue to layer in this manner.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix altogether and then chill for about an hour in refrigerator.
Then roll in balls and bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin; then add dry ingredients.
Mix in walnuts.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: scones
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and mayonnaise.
Stir sausage and cheese into flour mixture.
Make a well and add buttermilk all at once, using fork to stir to moisten.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead and pat dough out 3/4-inch thick.
Cut and bake on a cookie sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs, sugar, pumpkin and vanilla. Add to flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Place onions in bottom of greased baking dish.
Place hamburger on top of onions.
Cover with tomato soup.
Place creamed potatoes on top.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange-tossed strawberries
directions: Squeeze juice from orange halves over strawberries.
Toss strawberries and orange juice; divide into dessert dishes. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix(for water)
directions: Mix together in large container.
Store with lid on.
For one cup, put 4 tablespoons of mixture in cup, fill with hot water and stir.
Makes 25 cups.

title: frozen pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in gallon size freezer bags. Allow to thaw for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Break into pieces. This makes one punch bowl full.

title: basic potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes for 5 minutes or until tender.
While potatoes cook, mix all ingredients together.
Drain potatoes; mix well with all other ingredients.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Press in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix sour cream and milk with a mixer. Add in pudding mix until dissolved and then fold in Cool Whip. Spread half of mixture over crust. Slice 3 bananas on top and then put the other half of jello mixture on top. Grate pecans over top for garnish. You could also garnish with berries or shaved chocolate. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Toss, then dress with Italian dressing.
Marinate for at least 2 hours (best overnight).

title: 5-layer salad
directions: Mix lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion and peas.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over salad.
Cut up and fry bacon until crisp and sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over top.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: egg dumplings
directions: May also add baby limas, yellow split peas and/or soy beans.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cook squash
and onion in small amount of water.
Mash. Beat eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs to squash mixture. Add dry ingredients.
Mix.	Drop
from
spoon into hot oil or onto griddle with shallow oil.
Cook until done.

title: cheese torte
directions: Mix together and pat into greased spring-form pan.

title: bourbon chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Grate frozen margarine or butter over the chicken.
Add the two cans of cream of chicken soup over the chicken and sprinkle the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle dressing over the casserole.
Pour bourbon over dressing.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with vegetables or rice.

title: quick 'n easy cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in Dutch oven pan.
Add celery, onion, cabbage and green pepper; stir in rice.
Add remaining ingredients: tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Cover; reduce heat to simmer for 25 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan. Cook chicken until no longer pink, remove with slotted spoon. Cover and keep warm. Add onions to oil remaining in pan. Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in broth, green chilies, cumin, cilantro, oregano and red pepper. Reduce heat, and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes uncovered. Stir in chicken and kidney beans, simmer on low for 15 to 20 minutes. Garnish with Monterey Jack cheese. Also good with rice or cornbread.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain linguine. Add all other ingredients and toss.

title: zucchini-hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg lightly.
In greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole, put layer of hamburg, layer of onion, layer of zucchini and layer of tomatoes.
Sprinkle lightly with oregano.
Repeat layers again. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix cheese, chicken and green onions together.
In separate bowl, mix chicken soup, sour cream and green chilies together. Layer in casserole, starting with soup mix, tortillas, meat mix, etc.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with Spanish rice.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes slightly.
Mix potatoes, onion, soup and sour cream together and put into a pan.
Pour melted butter and crumbled potato chips on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and Eagle Brand milk in a large bowl. Add drained pineapple, mandarin oranges, miniature marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve fluffy on lettuce leaf or can be frozen and cut in squares.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Body: Canned peach half.

title: sour meat and dumplings
directions: Soak meat in vinegar and water to cover spices a week.
Drain well, saving liquid.
Brown meat in fat in heavy kettle.
Add salt and 1 1/2 cups of reserved liquid.
Cover and simmer slowly for 2 1/2 hours.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix with sour cream, mayonnaise, bacon bits and package of dressing.
Heat tortillas (per package instructions).
Roll spinach mixture in tortillas sushi-style. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.

title: chicken pollo
directions: Dust chicken in flour.
Fry in oil until golden.
Set aside. (Keep warm.)

title: hearty deep dish pizza(makes 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Press bread dough onto bottom and 1 inch up sides of 13 x 9-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Beat all ingredients together; knead with hands.
Shape into eggs and let set 1 hour. Coat with coating chocolate.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat with rotary or electric beater until just smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix until well blended.
Store in refrigerator in covered jar. Makes 1 cup.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Beat together egg yolks, powdered sugar and melted butter. Add Cool Whip. Crush the candy bars; save 1/2 for the top. Break angel food cake into pieces and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour mixture on top of cake; sprinkle with remaining candy.

title: lazy peach pie
directions: Melt butter in a 8x10-inch pyrex dish and set aside.

title: all-occasion punch
directions: Entire recipe will serve approximately 30 people.
Best to half recipe at a time.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Mix together and chill.
Spread over rolls, croissants or bread.

title: chocolate fudge filling
directions: Beat cream cheese and vanilla in small bowl until smooth. Slowly pour in corn syrup, beating until well blended.
Add chocolate; beat until smooth.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until well blended and smooth.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: nana's 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans; empty into bowl.
Add onions and garlic.
Combine all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour over beans; stir to coat.
Chill at least 12 hours, 24 hours is better.

title: my husband's mother's date pudding
directions: Mix dates, soda and water; let stand.
Mix well butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Add date mixture and pour into well-greased or wax paper and greased loaf pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Cover meat in flour mixture. Heat oil in a large skillet.
Brown flour covered meat in hot oil. Remove meat from pan.
Drain grease.
Return meat to pan.
Add onions and carrots.
Cover bottom of pan with water.
Reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender and carrots are done; adding water as needed.
Add a small amount of flour mixture to thicken for gravy if needed.

title: carolina hush puppies
directions: Mix; drop in hot oil 3 inches deep until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: red punch
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients while broccoli cooks according to directions on package.
Drain broccoli.
Place in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour mixture over top.
Crumble buttered Ritz crackers or stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marvelous microwave meat loaf
directions: Stir milk and egg together in a large bowl. Add bread crumbs and let stand several minutes to soften. Add remaining ingredients and stir with a fork to combine well.
Shape into a loaf in a 9 x 5-inch microwave-safe dish.
Place in microwave on Medium-high for 8 to 10 minutes. Turn dish and microwave for 11 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 150°.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: crabmeat dressing
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine until golden brown on low
heat.
Add
crabmeat,
soup, green onions and parsley.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Season to taste with red pepper, garlic salt and seasoned salt.
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs.
Pour into
buttered 3 quart oblong baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican picante chicken casserole
directions: Boil and season chicken as desired.
Save broth.
Remove chicken from bone.
Layer the chips, chicken and cheeses in casserole dish.
Combine the picante sauce and chicken broth and add to halfway up side of casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheeses turn brown.

title: olie's easy macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove to rack.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: quick and easy spaghetti
directions: Mix tomato sauce, paste and stewed tomatoes in saucepan.
Heat on medium; bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Add spices.
Brown ground beef.
Add to sauce.
Simmer 1/2 hours on low heat.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.
For less spicy, reduce spices. Serves 3 to 4.

title: easy jambalaya
directions: Drain tomatoes and corn, reserve liquid.
Add water to this and make 6 cups.
Place liquid and vegetables in a large saucepan and cook on stove, bringing mixture to a boil.
Add margarine, spices, rice and bacon; bring back to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cover and remove from the heat. Let stand 7 to 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mixing well, gradually add milk. Melt stick of margarine in casserole dish in oven.
Pour milk mixture over top of melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour can of peaches over top.
Do not stir.
Bake in 350 degree oven for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: liz's fudge
directions: Mix cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Add sugar, vanilla and pecans.
In the microwave, melt the white chocolate (can buy in bags that look like flat chips) and add to the mixture.
Work fast.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and keep in refrigerator until ready to cut and serve.

title: ann's squares
directions: Bring the sugar and Karo to a boil; remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chips in a double boiler.
Spread on pressed mixture.
Let cool at room temperature and cut.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sieve flour, baking powder and soda in a bowl.
Add wheat germ and bran, sugar and salt and mix all together.
Crumb in margarine or butter.
Make a well in the center of bowl and pour in buttermilk (and beaten egg); mix well, until mixture is one large piece of dough.
Sometimes extra buttermilk may be needed.
Turn onto greased tin.
Press down until required shape is obtained.
Make a cross on dough with a knife and brush top with a little milk.
Bake for 45 minutes. Test with a skewer.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on package, cool.
Mix mayonnaise, curry and oil from artichokes.
Add artichokes and mushrooms.
Toss lightly and refrigerate.
Better when made a day ahead.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all together in 9 by 13
pan.
Bake at 250°
for 15-20 min.
Stir a couple of times.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Blend butter, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll into balls and cool in refrigerator.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and allow to cool.

title: blueberry rhubarb crumble
directions: Crust:
Combine oats, brown sugar and 1/2 cup flour.
Work with a fork or knife and cut margarine into oat mixture.
Reserve 2/3 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Pat crumb mixture in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: date nut chocolate chip cake
directions: Soak dates, boiling water and soda.
Let cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add first mixture cooled.
Sift remaining ingredients and add.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chili dip in bread bowl
directions: Cut off top of bread, reserving the top. Scoop out inside of bread, leaving shell 1/2 to 1-inch thick. In bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, sour cream,

green onions, chilies, ham and Worcestershire sauce; mix well. This can be done ahead of time and when ready to bake, fill bread shell with mixture and cover the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove bread and serve with tortilla chips and bread chunks from inside and bread top.

title: apricot angel brownies
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring constantly until all of the chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until blended. Set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in chocolate mixture.
Combine apricots, almonds and coconut; stir half into the batter.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining apricot mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Empty blueberries into a strainer and wash.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except berries.
Mix well.
Gently fold in berries.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thaw strawberries; slice bananas.
Peel and slice kiwi.
Drain cherries, pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients into peach pie filling.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving for best taste.
Serves 6.
Keeps well.

title: double duty meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread 2/3 cup of the spaghetti sauce over bottom of 9 x 13 baker.
Chop onion.
In 2-quart bowl, combine onion, ground beef, oats, 1/3 cup of sauce, egg, garlic, Italian seasoning and salt; mix gently.
Using a small scoop, shape meat mixture into balls.
Place in 9 x 13 baker.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour remaining sauce over meatballs.
Continue baking 20 minutes.
Place 24 meatballs and half of the sauce from baker in covered container; refrigerate for later use in spaghetti.
Use remaining 24 in sub sandwich.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: taco chili
directions: Cook meat until done. Add 1 1/2 cups water, taco seasoning and Ranch mix. Combine all ingredients and cook until hot.

title: chocolate drink
directions: Blend together ice cream and milk.
Add cookie and blend until coarsely crushed.
Serves 2.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing per directions in microwave.
Make in oven safe casserole.
In medium saucepan, heat soup with 1/2 can of water over medium-high heat until smooth.
Add chicken and 1/2 can onions to soup.
Allow to cook until edges of chicken turn white. Spread broccoli pieces over stuffing.
Cover broccoli and stuffing with soup/chicken mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and spread remainder of onion.
Return to oven and allow onions to brown.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients for filling in order given.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: holiday banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except lemon-lime drink. Freeze this in shallow pan. When ready to serve, break frozen mixture up into chunks and add 2 bottles of lemon-lime drink. Mixture will smooth out as the drink blends with it. Makes 30 cups.

title: crock-pot pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in a bag; shake steaks.
Put in crock-pot.
Pour the remaining flour mixture on top.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and turn crock-pot to high for 1 hour.
Reduce to low and cook for 9 to 10 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chex party mix
directions: In large 4-quart bowl or a (13 x 9 x 2-inch) glass dish, melt butter on High for 1 minute.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Gradually add cereal and nuts, mixing until all pieces are coated.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Or bake in roasting pan for 1 hour at 250° in oven.
Spread on absorbent paper towel to cool.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 10 minutes.
Mix nuts, coconut, milk, melted butter and vanilla wafers.
Fold the eggs and butter mix together gently.
Bake in greased tube pan for 60 minutes at 375°.

title: sugar pickle for ham
directions: Boil the salt, saltpetre, saliratus and sugar or molasses. Skim.
Let cool.
Then pour it over the meat; the meat is to remain in pickle from 4 to 6 weeks.

title: mo's chili
directions: Put meat into heavy skillet (or cast-iron pot).
Cook all the moisture out of meat until slightly browned.
Add tomato juice and water (for desired consistency).
Simmer until meat shows signs of tenderness.
Add chili powder, onion, black pepper, salt, cumin and garlic.
Continue to cook until meat is thoroughly tender.

title: sausage and egg brunch casserole
directions: Saute and drain sausage.
Beat eggs with milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Cube bread and layer cubes, sausage and cheese in buttered 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Use equal parts of chicken broth and milk.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add to hot broth and milk mixture to thicken.
Saute celery and onions (in butter).
Add to mixture. Add frozen box of spinach which has been thawed first.
Add sliced fresh mushrooms, white pepper and celery salt.

title: party crackers
directions: Mix the Ranch dressing, oil and dill weed.
Pour mixture over the crackers that have been placed in a 1 gallon jug with a tight fitting lid.
Turn upside down very gently until mixture coats crackers.
Turn every hour for 1 day.
The longer they sit, the better they taste, but are ready to sample after 2 hours. Delicious alone or as an hors d'oeuvre with any type cheese topping.

title: dave's dish
directions: Cook macaroni as directed, lightly brown ground beef and onion.
Add corn, soup, cheese, tomatoes and peppers.
Mix with macaroni.
Heat in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: t-j miracle soup
directions: Boil, covered with water.
Turn on low heat until soft.
Eat soup any time!!

title: icebox pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers, onions and pepper in jars.
Mix sugar, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers.
Turn upside-down in refrigerator.
Makes one gallon.

title: easy cake
directions: Use 9 x 13 baking dish or close. Spray with Pam. Spread cherry pie filling on bottom. Spread crushed pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over this. Pour melted butter over all. Top with nuts and coconut. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into graham cracker pie shell. Serve chilled.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature.
Cream the Cool Whip and cream cheese together and fold in all ingredients.
Set in refrigerator for 6 hours.

title: thick peach diet shake
directions: Process peaches, milk, Equal and flavoring in a blender.
Add ice cubes, one at a time, and blend on high speed.
Twelve ounces have 75 calories.
You may substitute bananas or strawberries for the peaches.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar well.
Add vanilla pudding mix and milk.
Mix until well blended and thick, then spoon in Cool Whip. Crumble up fine some Oreo cookies and make first layer in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then follow with filling.
Then another layer of Oreos and then filling.

title: cheese and pasta
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook and drain macaroni shells.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: great spareribs
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix and season with salt and red pepper.
Cool in refrigerator.
Make little straws by rolling in your hand or roll out with rolling pin and make cookies.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: lolly's shrimp salad
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: fruit cups
directions: Mix all together and freeze in small plastic cups for snacks. Eat while partially frozen.

title: waldorf astoria cake(like a red devil's food cake)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and coloring. Then add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix vinegar and baking soda; fold in.
Bake two layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add vanilla extract, then gradually add the sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in sour cream until mixture thickens.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix thoroughly until mixture is thick.
Spoon into graham crusts, leveling as you go.
Top with sliced strawberries.
Place in fridge for 12 hours. Makes 2 cakes.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, milk and oleo.
Turn heat off.
Mix the mixture with the oatmeal and cocoa.
Stir.
Place teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: green bean pizza
directions: Place all ingredients in a skillet and cover.
Heat just until cheese turns light brown.
This is one of those recipes that sounds awful but tastes great and is so easy and quick to fix.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with chow mein noodles and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, grated, to sugar and let set for 1 hour.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Add nuts and dry ingredients.
Add apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not overbake.

title: no-knead tupperware bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 7-quart Tupperware container; let stand 5 minutes.
Add flour and next 4 ingredients, stirring well to blend.
Cover container with lid and seal.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour or until lid pops off.
Spoon dough evenly into 3 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Coat with cooking spray.
Cover to rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until sounds hollow.

title: quick bread mix
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Store in covered container up to 6 weeks. For longer storage, place in freezer.
To measure, spoon into cup and level with spatula.

title: spicy apple twist
directions: Slice apples into 8 pieces each.
Cut rolls into 16 pieces. Place 1 apple slice in wide end and roll up.
Place in a 9-inch square pan with juice on bottom.
Drizzle margarine over rolls. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: famous lemon pecan pie
directions: Combine first
six ingredients.
Mix with fork or whisk (do not use electric mixer).
Stir in pecan pieces.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: *cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and gradually add 1 cup of sugar and the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with milk, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons sugar with cinnamon.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt until smooth.
Beat eggs until yellow.
Add sugar and the cornstarch mixture along with vanilla and the milk.
Cook until done (thickened).
Cool.
(Add fruit, if desired).
Freeze in churn.

title: herring dumplings
directions: Grind potatoes, herring and onions.
Add wheat hearts or oatmeal, thyme, pepper and baking powder.
Add flour enough to make stiff dough so balls hold their shape.
Drop dumplings into boiling water to which vinegar has been added.
Cook1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Cubes of salt pork may be put in center of balls.
Serve with melted bacon fat and fried bacon, or melted butter.

title: cheese daisies
directions: Cream shortening and cheese together.
Sift pepper and salt with flour, then add.
Chill for 1/2 hour before rolling out.
Cut with small biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes. Yields 24.

title: soft laundry soap(note:  use rubber gloves)
directions: Slowly empty contents of 1 can of lye into 2 1/2 pints cold water in an iron or enamel vessel. Stir occasionally until dissolved, being careful not to inhale too much.
Allow to cool to lukewarm.

title: pheasant
directions: Cut pheasant up like you would a chicken.
Brown pieces in butter and chopped onion.
Pour sauce over browned pieces, bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onions. Shape into balls. Blend soup and water in pressure cooker until it starts to simmer. Add meat balls. Cook at 15 pounds 10 minutes.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and egg.
Mix until well blended; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined oil and eggs, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Reserve 2 cups batter; pour remaining into greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan.

Pour cream cheese mixture over batter; carefully spoon reserved batter over cream cheese mixture, spreading to cover. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut cake
directions: Cream oleo and gradually add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Beat 10 minutes on electric mixer.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs one at a time to creamed mixture, beating well.
Add flour; mix alternately with milk and vanilla. Beat after each addition.
Batter should be smooth.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: divinity or seafoam
directions: Boil sugar and syrup to hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites and salt until stands in peaks.
Pour into syrup while still beating slowly.
Add vanilla; beat until dull and loses glossy look, then add nuts.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 27 to 30 pieces.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients; mix well.
Make into small balls, about 1/2 inch in diameter.
Cook in skillet for about 7 or 8 minutes until brown, turning once.
Remove from skillet; drain on paper towels.
Mix chili sauce and jelly in saucepan; heat on medium heat.
Put meatballs in sauce; heat thoroughly.

title: famous tar heel hush puppies
directions: Stir, adding water, to thick consistency.
Drop in deep fat. Cook in temperature of 375°.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add rest of ingredients to sausage.
Add sausage to cheese.
Spread on top of bread slices.
Put on cookie sheet and broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Can be frozen and then broiled for 10 minutes.

title: in clover's lace cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add brown sugar, stirring well, with a large spoon.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Drop by level teaspoon on a well-buttered nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 5 minutes.
Watch closely, they should be golden brown.
Let cool for 30 seconds and remove with spatula onto a rack to cool.
If cookies mash together, they are too warm.
If they stick and break, they are too cool and need to be reheated.
Can be stored in airtight container and frozen. Makes 10 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix well with stuffing mix.
Place 1/3 in casserole dish.
Put 1/2 of cut-up chicken over stuffing.
Mix 1 can chicken broth and cream of chicken soup and pour over chicken. Put 1/3 stuffing over soup mix and rest of chicken pieces over stuffing.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Put rest of stuffing on top and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: party pinwheels
directions: You will need party toothpicks.
Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread onto tortillas; then roll tortilla.
Slice filled, rolled tortillas into bite-sized pieces, arranging on platter with party toothpicks.
Place picante sauce in serving bowl for dip.

title: mini reubens
directions: Arrange pumpernickel bread slices on cookie sheet.
Top each piece of bread with 1/2 teaspoon of Thousand Island dressing. Next, put about 1 teaspoon of sauerkraut on each slice of bread and top with small amounts of corned beef and Swiss cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll in a ball and press out with hand. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture on top of cookie and press down with hand.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, depending on your oven, at 300° to 325° on top rack.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and butter over heat.
When warm, stir in slowly the eggs, well beaten.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
When ready to serve, add 1 cup whipped cream.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream butter and add sugar, vanilla and water.
Sift together flour and salt; stir into butter mixture.
Add pecans and mix thoroughly.
Using portions about the size of a small walnut, roll into crescent shape.
Bake in slow oven, 325°, about 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
It's not Christmas without them.

title: swedish pie
directions: Crush crackers.
Whip egg whites; fold mixture of nuts, sugar and crackers into egg whites-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cocoa, vanilla and milk.
Heat and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop teaspoonfuls on wax paper and chill.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: On a cutting board, place each chicken wing and cut off tip of first joint; discard or save for stock.
Cut the remaining wing into two parts at the joint.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In deep fryer or heavy saucepan, place oil and heat to high temperature.
Add half the wings; cook, stirring occasionally, for about 10 minutes, or until golden brown and crisp.
Remove chicken from oil; drain on paper towels.
Cook remaining wings, repeating process.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Use a little extra Sweet 10 for more flavor.

title: no-crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into two greased 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 2 pies.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Melt together Eagle Brand milk and caramels.
Then dip marshmallow (one at a time) into this mixture and roll in chopped pecans.

title: mike's macaroni and cheese ala italiano
directions: Cook macaroni according to package, use salt in cooking water (a lot).
Cook until medium soft (do not overcook).
Drain. Place in oblong baking dish.
Put butter in milk and microwave until butter is melted and milk is warm.
Pour over macaroni. Dust flour and seasonings over top of mixture.
Add cheeses and mix in thoroughly.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes or until top is brown and crusty.
Leftovers are great.

title: banana-oatmeal bread
directions: Mix together in order given.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff or in peaks.
Crush crackers and fold into mixture.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake 30 minutes at 325°. Let cool and top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: quick sweet rolls
directions: Melt butter in round cake pan.
Add dark brown sugar and water.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over.
Cut up biscuits; quarter each biscuit.
Bake according to directions on can.
Turn over immediately onto plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 8 minutes in boiling salted water; drain. Mix soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and egg with broccoli.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°
then sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and blend until smooth. Store in refrigerator.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in covered bowl in refrigerator.
No need to let rise. Bake as biscuits.
Bake at 375° to 400°.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator for a week to 10 days.

title: tortellini with pesto and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions. Drain and toss with pesto, sun-dried tomatoes, chopped basil and cheese. Serve hot or at room temperature. Serves 4.

title: shaker lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and salt in saucepan; add water.
Beat egg yolks; add to sugar mixture.
Cook over hot water, stirring until thickened.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes.
Add margarine, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spoon meringue over pie filling.
Bake in a 400° oven until meringue is brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix Knorr vegetable soup, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add the frozen spinach but make sure it is drained well.
Mix.
Then add water chestnuts and mix.
Let set for 2 hours.
Serve with Hawaiian bread or pumpernickel bread.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco and add yeast and milk; mix well.
Let set in refrigerator until needed.
Drop by spoonful or roll in flour.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well and add to starter.
Let stand out of refrigerator all day (5 to 12 hours).
Mixture will be very bubbly.
Take out 1 cup to make bread and return to refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days and feed again.
If not making bread after feeding starter, throw away 1 cup or give to a friend.
(This is to avoid deflating your starter.)
(Note every third feeding, take out 2 cups and make 2 batches of bread or give away 1 cup to keep the starter from building up and deflating.)

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion lightly in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add all of ingredients in large kettle.
Add 1 1/2 quarts water and simmer slowly, about 1 hour.

title: pecan-coated cheese balls
directions: Let cheeses warm to room temperature.
Then beat together until light and fluffy and blended.
Beat in onion and garlic. Chill.
Roll into a ball, then roll in chopped nuts until well coated.
Keep in refrigerator until needed.
Spread on crackers.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Microwave at 30% for 4 minutes; let stand 2 minutes.
Stir in soda and nuts.
Pour over popcorn; mix until well coated.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook chicken, cool and pick from bone.
Cook broccoli, drain; cool.
Mix soups and mayonnaise in blender.
Layer, beginning with broccoli, chicken, then soup mixture.
End with soup mixture.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (until bubbly).

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Cook strawberries and 1 cup of sugar for 10 minutes.
Add 2 more cups of sugar and cook 10 more minutes to rolling boil.
Put in crock or porcelain to cool; stir.
Let stand overnight.
Put in jars and cover with wax.

title: tuna fish special
directions: In a bowl, combine tuna, peas, celery and onions.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce, curry powder and garlic powder; stir into tuna mixture.
Stir in almonds; top with noodles.
Serve on lettuce if desired.
Serves 2.

title: sauerkraut, sausage and potato casserole
directions: Pour undrained sauerkraut into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Toss with onion and brown sugar.
Bury sausage pieces in sauerkraut.
Peel potatoes; cut in half lengthwise and arrange on top.
Brush with margarine; sprinkle with salt and paprika. Bake at 425°, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Tightly cover with foil.
Bake until potatoes are cooked through, 20 to 30 minutes. Serve at once from baking dish.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add eggs; beat smooth.
Stir in rhubarb.
Fill 9-inch pie crust; dot filling with 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Cover with one 9-inch pie crust.

title: julienne vegetable plate
directions: In mixing bowl, blend together mayonnaise or salad dressing and Blue cheese.
Add milk and lemon juice, beating until smooth. Chill.
Serve with chilled vegetables arranged on platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lime slime
directions: Add ingredients one at a time until well mixed.
Mix together and put in refrigerator.

title: club sandwiches
directions: Toast bread; spread with butter. Cover 8 slices with chicken. Cover chicken with more bread slices, each one spread with mayonnaise. Place 2 slices bacon and 2 slices tomato on top of each sandwich and cover with remaining toast. Fasten securely with long toothpicks. Cut each sandwich diagonally into 4 triangles and stand them upright on a plate. Serves 8.

title: spicy salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Add Jell-O and applesauce; let cool.
Put in a square pan.
When congealed, cut into squares.

title: frozen cherry delight
directions: Mix together pie filling, pineapple and sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9x13-inch pyrex dish. Freeze for 1 hour or until hard.
Cut into squares when ready to serve.

title: chilaquile casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Heat oil in medium skillet over medium-low heat; add onions and garlic and cook 5 minutes until tender. Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Spread half the tortillas along bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle half the cheese and 1 can chilies over top. Sprinkle onion mixture over chilies. Repeat layering remaining tortillas, cheese and chilies. Whisk eggs, buttermilk, salt, pepper, cumin and oregano in medium bowl. Pour over casserole. Bake 45 minutes until set and browned on top. Makes 6 servings. Prep time: 20 minutes. Baking time: 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Good alone or with caramel frosting.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine cream cheese with pineapple juice, blending well. Drain orange slices.
Add with marshmallows and bananas; mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and coconut; mix lightly.
Chill about 30 minutes and serve.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Mix together the cornbread crumbs, onion, croutons, 1/2 cup chicken pieces and the broth in a large bowl.
Press lightly into a greased pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, pickle or pickle relish, onion, parsley, pimiento and lemon juice.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Serve with fish or seafood.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in plastic bag.
Wash and clean chicken. Take chicken pieces and place in plastic bag; shake until well coated.
Place chicken, skin side down, on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Turn chicken and bake for 1/2 hour more.

title: scones(scottish)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend dry ingredients using pastry cutter.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Handling as little as possible, drop by large spoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Cook 20 minutes or until light brown.
Serve plain with marmalade or lemon curd.

title: western burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add catsup, mustard and olives. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Turn off heat and add cheese. Spread on buns and wrap each in foil. Can be frozen for later use. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, 45 if frozen.

title: stripe-it-rich pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Remove from oven.
Poke holes quickly down through cake with round handle of wooden spoon at 1-inch intervals (or use a plastic straw using a turning motion to make large holes).
Only after poking holes, combine pudding mix with sugar in a large bowl. Gradually stir in milk. Beat at low speed of electric mixer for not more than 1 minute (do not overbeat).
Quickly, before pudding thickens, pour about half of the thin pudding evenly over warm cake and into the holes to make the stripes. Allow remaining pudding to thicken slightly.
Spoon over the top, swirling it to frost the cake.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Store cake in refrigerator. Cover with plastic wrap, if desired.

title: hearty potato sauerkraut soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil, then reduce to simmer until vegetables are tender.
Garnish with bacon and hard-boiled eggs, if desired.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar; add vanilla and sour milk. Beat well with mixer.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well; stir in diced zucchini.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean and dry.

title: cashaw lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Fill two pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Lightly steam vegetables until tender-crisp.
Melt margarine. Add minced garlic.
Saute lightly.
Toss noodles and vegetables. Pour garlic butter over; toss to mix.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham and egg toss
directions: Combine ham, eggs, celery and gherkins.
Blend remaining ingredients; add to ham mixture. Toss lightly.
Season with salt and pepper, chill.

title: applesauce rice
directions: Bring Water, Applesauce, Margarine, Salt and Cinnamon to boil in medium sauce pan.
Stir in Rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Apple.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: shortie
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl until dough forms a ball.
(If too buttery, add flour; if too dry, add butter.)
Pat out on board (not floured) 1/2-inch thick.
Prick with fork.
Cut into squares or shapes and place on cookie sheet.
Place in 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream with mixer.
Add butter and seasonings.
Put into greased casserole.
Brush top with butter; sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or can be refrigerated overnight and baked the next day for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients together; cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, bake white or yellow Duncan Hines cake according to directions on package.
Split layers and spread with coconut mixture.
Frost top and sides of cake with coconut mixture.
Cover with dry coconut and refrigerate in airtight container.
Let set a day before eating.

title: zucchini chicken
directions: Place all ingredients except chicken and zucchini in shallow roasting pan and put the chicken on top; brush with melted butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Add zucchini, thinly sliced.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Remove chicken, zucchini and lemon.
Mix 2 tablespoons of cornstarch and 1/2 cup cool chicken bouillon or water until smooth.
Pour into pan, stirring constantly and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Serve around chicken pieces on large platter.
Serves 4.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Bring tomato juice to a boil and add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt bars and 1 stick oleo; set aside.
Cream sugar and the other stick of oleo; add milk and vanilla.
Stir in melted ingredients, pour into 15 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange-raisin honey buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Pour honey evenly and scatter raisins over honey.
In small bowl, combine rest of butter with orange peel.
Separate biscuits.
From each into a ball.
Dip each ball into butter mixture to coat, then dip in nuts.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Slice 4
bell
peppers	into
strips
and parboil until tender.
Place a
layer
of cracker crumbs in a 2-quart casserole dish;
then a layer of pepper strips.
Cover with a layer of shredded
American	cheese and 1/2 can of cream of mushroom soup to which
a
bit of milk has been added along with a dash of Worcestershire sauce and a dash of cayenne.
Repeat layers: peppers, cheese
and
soup.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and brown on top.

title: rocket fuel
directions: Measure one shot each of all liquors.
Measure two shots of orange juice.
Stir to mix and refrigerate.

title: crab bisque
directions: Melt the butter in a large saucepan, then stir in the flour, salt and pepper.
Add the milk and bouillon gradually, while stirring.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add crabmeat, onion and parsley.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain, forcing as much of the crab through the sieve as possible.
Add the cream and reheat. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to margarine mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Bake at 350°.
Pecans and dates are optional, but it's very good.

title: stuffed tortillas
directions: Mix softened cheese and dressing until spreads easily on tortillas.
Layer remaining ingredients on top of cheese mixture. Roll tightly.
Chill overnight, then slice to serve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spoon into buttered loaf pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Serve with Cream Sauce hot or cold.

title: orchard apple crisp
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Arrange in an ungreased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Combine oats, brown sugar, flour and salt. Cut in butter and sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown and bubbly and apples are tender.
Serve warm with milk or ice cream.

title: tandy kake(most wanted food)
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 to 30 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix cooked rice and sugar; let set until liquid forms.
Cut marshmallows in small pieces and add to rice with crushed pineapple and cream (whipped).
Chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together meal, flour and salt in large bowl.
Mix in onion.
Stir in milk, then stir in egg.
Let mixture stand 3 minutes.
Cook at 360°.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
You may frost with your favorite frosting or serve plain.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until thick. Stir in grated zucchini.
Add remaining dry ingredients and stir. Fold in the chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into 2 oiled and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
(May use disposable pans or nonstick.) Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool loaves in pans for 10 minutes.
Invert onto rack and cool completely.
Loaves may be frozen.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove from water; cool.
Bone chicken and cut into pieces.
Cool broccoli and drain.
Arrange in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole; top with cooked chicken.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in large saucepan.
Remove from heat; add all other ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan (18 x 12-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage and bacon
directions: Cook shredded cabbage in salted, boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Fry chopped bacon in large frying pan.
Remove bacon and drain fat.
Melt the butter in the pan.
Stir in flour and blend with remaining fat.
Add milk.
Stir until smooth and cook until thickened.
Return cabbage and bacon; toss together.
Season to taste.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Combine black-eyed peas, tomatoes and okra.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in margarine.
Combine with black-eyed pea mixture in a crock-pot.
Simmer on low, 6 to 8 hours.

title: burger bean bake
directions: Cook diced bacon.
Remove meat from pan, drain most of bacon fat, then brown the ground meat and onions.
Drain most of the fat off.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in casserole dish, cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Then beat until thick the cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip and drained pineapple.
Put on cool cake.
Best on yellow sheet cake.

title: salsa
directions: Blend all ingredients and cook 20 minutes. Add water to desired consistency while cooking. Makes 2 quarts.

title: cheddar quiche
directions: Make your own crust or buy ready-made crust and prepare as directed.
Cut cheese in
to
8 slices (3 x 4 x 1/8-inch thick).
Cover bottom
of
pie
shell
with cheese overlapping slices.
Set aside	1/2
cup
French
fried
onions;
sprinkle remainder over cheese.
Sprinkle
on
celery, green pepper and bacon.
In a
mixing bowl beat together eggs and mustard until blended;
add milk.
Pour
into pie shell;	bake approximately 45 minutes or	until
a
knife
inserted near center comes out clean. Remove pie
from
oven,
sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese. Allow to stand 20 minutes before serving.
Meanwhile, heat 1/2 cup of the reserved
onions
in
oven	until crisp and golden brown. Garnish top
with onions. Cut pie in generous wedges to serve.

title: ham slice in orange sauce
directions: Place ham in a large nonstick skillet. Combine orange juice and remaining 4 ingredients, stirring well. Pour over ham. Cook over medium heat 4 minutes on each side or until ham is heated and sauce thickens slightly, basting often with sauce. Discard cloves before serving. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: greek cheeseburgers
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, Feta cheese, cumin and mint just until blended. Shape into 4 (4-inch) round patties. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: coated coconut candy
directions: Mix sugar and coconut together.
Melt butter and cool.
Add vanilla and milk.
Pour over sugar and coconut.
Shape into balls. Place in refrigerator 1 hour.
Melt 1 box of unsweetened Baker's chocolate with 1/3 block paraffin.
