Dip balls into chocolate, using a toothpick.
Place on wax paper until chocolate hardens.

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients (except cornflakes and margarine) and place in a greased pan.
Top with cornflakes and coat with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: mini cheddar cheese biscuits(1 dozen)
directions: Combine biscuit mix and cheese.
Stir in garlic and milk until just moistened.

title: aunt mae's liver pate ball
directions: Mix 1/2 cream cheese with other ingredients in blender or mixer.
Form ball and chill.
When firm, mix remaining cream cheese with milk and frost ball.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, quarter and cook potatoes.
Drain and return pan to low heat, shaking to dry potatoes.
In large bowl of electric mixer, cream together softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Add hot potatoes one at a time to cream mixture and continue beating at high speed until light and fluffy.
On low speed, add green onions, celery, green pepper, parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder and melted butter.
Spoon into 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until heated through and top is golden.

title: hidden secret
directions: Line 11 x 16-inch pan with foil.
Spray or grease.
Arrange single layer crackers in pan.
Boil margarine and sugar for 10 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until crackers float and bubble.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chips.
After chips are melted, spread like frosting.
Sprinkle with
nuts.
Separate with knife.
Place in fridge to cool.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a saucepan.
Add water and cook until mixture has a clear look to it.
Let it cool.

title: almond salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over green salad.
Top with toasted sliced almonds.

title: tangy potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes; add lemon juice and mix to keep potatoes from turning dark.
Dice 4 eggs, celery and olives.
Mix all together. Add enough
mayonnaise to hold together.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add vinegar to taste.
Add crumbled bacon. Refrigerate.
Should have a tangy taste.

title: barbecue meatballs and sauce
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs and set aside.
Mix salt and pepper with ground beef and bread mixture and make into balls. Place in baking dish.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Sift together baking soda, salt and flour.
Mix thoroughly the oil, sugar and 100% bran cereal; add water and let cool.
When mixture is cool, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add buttermilk and bran cereal; beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in raisins and All-Bran cereal.
Store in refrigerator for 12 hours before using.
Will keep 3 weeks.
Use as needed.
Do not stir before using; spoon into muffin tins, filling about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes, or until done.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add dressing and crackers.
Let set 2 hours and chill.

title: clam bisque
directions: Drain mushrooms and clams.
Reserve liquid.
Saute mushrooms, clams and onions in butter for 10 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in half and half; bring it to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour half of mixture in blender, blending until smooth.
Return to saucepan and heat.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Mix pudding and milk; put over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip, nuts and chocolate shavings.

title: snappy cheese wafers
directions: Work flour, salt, cayenne and Tabasco sauce into soft oleo. Add grated sharp cheese.
Mix well. Add the Rice Krispies. Drop by small teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet and pat slightly. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry the onions and hamburger; drain.
Add olive oil.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl.
Put the mixture in the pie crust. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add butter, sugar, milk, salt, and lemon rind.
Form into 8 balls, using marshmallow as center of each.
Roll in corn flakes and bake in buttered baking dish at 425 degrees until brown and marshmallow begins to ooze.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Beat in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Spread into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Marinate in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Place layer of asparagus mixture in greased casserole.
Put half of crushed crackers, another layer of asparagus and remainder of cracker crumbs.
Top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oriental rice
directions: Lightly brown
1/2 cups uncooked brown rice in a dry skillet.
Add 4
cups boiling water, cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes, until
done.
Do
not
stir.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chalupa
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in large pot (crock-pot) and cover with water. Cook, covered, on low heat, and if necessary, add water. After 6 hours, take out bones and break up roast with fork. Cook with lid off until thick, about 1 hour. Serve mixture over bed of corn chips (Fritos) and add any or all of the other ingredients.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Saute shrimp, bell pepper, celery and onion in small amount of oil.
Add soup and rice.
Pour in casserole dish; season as desired with plenty of red pepper.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In Dutch oven over medium heat, in hot butter/margarine, cook peas and next 5 ingredients; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in next 6 ingredients; cook 20 minutes, or until macaroni is tender.
Salt to taste; serve with cheese.
Makes 15 cups or 8 servings.

title: poppy seed scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (skins on) until tender.
Cool, peel and grate. Stir all ingredients together.
Add enough milk to make "squishy." Sprinkle very generously with poppy seed.
Bake 1 hour at 300°. (Freezes well.)

title: beef brisket
directions: Combine liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, celery seed and brown sugar; add brisket.
If brisket isn't mostly covered, add some water and ketchup.
Let set overnight in shallow pan.
Place brisket in roaster pan; seal top with foil.
Cook at 300° for 4 or 5 hours.
Uncover.
Add barbecue sauce if desired and cook 1 more hour.
Remove meat.
Let cool.
Remove fat.
Add two tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup water to meat sauce.
Allow meat to cool before slicing.
Slice across the grain very thin.

title: dump cake
directions: Put the pineapple and pie filling into an ungreased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Stir together and then add cake mix.
Slice the oleo and put spread out on top of the mix.
Top with crushed walnuts.
Bake in oven at 350° for 60 minutes, best in middle of the oven.
Can serve with Cool Whip.

title: murray's chili
directions: Cook beans and spaghetti in large pot using enough water for spaghetti (do not drain).
Brown hamburger meat.
Add pepper, onion, salt, garlic salt, chili powder and tomatoes.
Mix together and cook until all ingredients are done.
Add meat mixture to beans and spaghetti.
This makes a big pot of chili.
I put it in pint containers and freeze.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and cover with water; boil for 5 minutes.
Mix together ground chuck, salt, celery salt, pepper, ketchup, eggs and crackers.
Put chopped onions on the bottom of a small roaster or large dish.
Drain cabbage and leaves off.
Roll a small handful of meat mixture up in a leaf of cabbage.
Lay rolls, flap side down, onto onions.
Heat jelly and chili sauce until it is liquid.
Pour over Cabbage Rolls.
Use left over cabbage juice to keep rolls from drying out.
Bake at 350° with lid for 1 1/2 hours, 1/2 hour without lid.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Alternately add flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla flavoring.

title: easy peanut butter cookies(holiday recipe)
directions: Combine.
Roll into balls; flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sesame cumin bow ties
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine cumin and salt.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the salt mixture and 1 tablespoon of the sesame seed over lightly floured work surface.
Place pastry on top.
Sprinkle pastry with remaining salt mixture and sesame seed.
Roll pastry into a rectangle approximately 11 x 14-inch.
While rolling pastry, press sesame seed into the pastry.
With a sharp knife, cut pastry crosswise into strips about 1 inch wide and cut each long strip into 4 short ones.
Take each strip, twist and pinch center to form a bow tie.
Place about 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Beat egg white with 1 tablespoon of water and brush over top of bow ties. Bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes 52 bow ties.

title: rich corn cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt; mix well.
Quickly add the sour cream, milk, eggs and butter. Mix.
Spoon into pans and bake 20 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: hawkesbury steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Place in large shallow casserole.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice and arrange on top of steak.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and celery.
Combine reserved juice with remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In large roasting pan, keep popcorn warm.
Melt butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in pot and let boil until hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and peanuts. Drizzle syrup over corn and stir.
Bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil together the oleo, water and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat well and bake on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and ritz
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take out bones.
Mix broth, celery, cheese, onion, eggs and soup, then add chicken, crackers, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.
Serves 20 people.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Break cake in 1/2 and small pieces. Place in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix 1 package of pudding as directed on box and pour over cake.
Drain one can of pineapple and pour over pudding.
Next, put one can cherry pie filling, then 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Add nuts (if desired).
Repeat layers and top with nuts and cherries.

title: dilly beans
directions: Cook beans for 3 minutes.
(Have water boiling when you put beans in.)
Place 1 head of dill, 1 garlic clove and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in each jar (4 jars); pack beans in jars.
In a saucepan, combine water, vinegar, salt and sugar; bring to a boil and pour over beans.
Seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: hot milk sponge
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add baking powder and vanilla and mix. Add flour and heated milk.
Pour into a greased and floured pan (tube).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or loaf pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: county raisin rye bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 1 cup whole wheat flour, 1 cup rye flour, yeast and salt.
In a saucepan, heat water, 1/2 cup oil, molasses and honey to 120° to 130°.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Stir in remaining whole wheat and rye flours and enough all purpose flour to form a medium stiff dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; sprinkle with raisins.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Grease a bowl with remaining oil.
Place dough in bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down, turn onto a lightly floured surface.
Divide into four pieces; shape each into a round loaf.
Place 4 inches apart on two baking sheets coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 loaves of bread.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls, put on cookie sheets and press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 12-15 minutes.
Be sure not to over cook.
Cook until the bottom of wafer is golden brown.

title: cheese balls
directions: Use your hands to mix the cheese and parsley flakes thoroughly.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll each cheese ball in the ground nuts.
Refrigerate until 1/2 hour before serving time. Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain liquid from cherries and pineapple.
Heat liquid and dissolve jello in it.
Add unchilled Coke. Let set until thick and add other ingredients.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients, in the order listed, in a large bowl.
Can be made several hours ahead.
Stir well before serving.

title: paw paw's barbecue chicken
directions: Pour barbecue sauce and Coke over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and let simmer for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add applesauce, then sift dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth and fold in raisins.
Bake in wax paper lined 8-inch square pan in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve plain or frosted. This cake will remain moist for several days in a tightly covered container.

title: super peanutty layer cake
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: tuna mushroom a la king
directions: In saucepan, cook celery and onion until tender.
Blend in soup; stir in other ingredients.
Heat and stir; serve over toast or noodles.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl mix together brown sugar, flour and walnuts.
Stir in melted butter until well mixed.
Set aside 1/3 of the crumbs for topping.
Pat remainder gently into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add crushed pineapple.
Stir in cubed bread.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until lightly browned.
A dash of cinnamon may be sprinkled over casserole before putting in oven.

title: chili biscuits
directions: Put hamburger in heavy saucepan with tight lid; cook until tender, about 40 minutes in its own juice, stirring often.
Saute onion and Crisco.
Add chili powder, cumin, salt, pepper, garlic powder, paprika and Accent.
Add the onion and seasonings to steamed meat.
Add 3 cups of boiling water and stir well.
Cover and allow to simmer 20 minutes.
Cook and fill top of biscuits with chili mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of chili biscuits.
Put in oven long enough to melt cheese.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheesy tuna chowder
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add cheese soup; gradually blend in milk.
Add undrained tomatoes, undrained tuna, parsley and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese and sausage grits(brunch)
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add Tabasco sauce, garlic and pepper to
sausage.
Cook grits in 2 cups boiling water.	Add all ingredients together, stirring until mixed.
Pour mixture into
a well
buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan drops
directions: Blend the oleo, salt, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Add the flour and pecans.
Mix until all the flour is damp.
Make into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press.
(You may add a cherry to the top if you want to.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Slice chicken into 1 x 1-inch pieces.
Saute mushrooms.
Soak chicken in egg for 1 hour.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in butter.
Place chicken and juices into casserole dish. Cover with mushroom and chicken broth.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granny's chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat eggs and add sugar. Pour in cooled butter, vinegar, vanilla, milk and cornmeal. Mix thoroughly. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Reduce to 350° and bake 50 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat cider in 6-quart saucepan over low heat for 15 minutes. Add candy. Heat for 15 minutes or until candy has dissolved, stirring constantly. Serve hot. May keep warm in coffee pot. Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon yogurt mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add cold water to reserved syrup to make 2/3 cup. Stir syrup into gelatin; cool.
With rotary beater, beat yogurt into gelatin; chill until partially set.
Fold in fruit and cucumber.
Pour into 4-cup mold; chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange lemonade
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves.
Cool. Add juices and peel to cooled sugar syrup.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Strain syrup; cover and refrigerate.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Simmer all ingredients together until water is cooked in.

title: cheese onion bread
directions: Saute onions until tender.
Mix egg, corn and milk to make a soft dough.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top dough with onions, sour cream and lastly with grated cheese.

title: no stir cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Gradually add milk to mixture, stirring until fairly smooth.
Spoon batter evenly over melted butter. Remove peaches from can with fork.
Place on top of batter.
Drizzle peach juice over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: too easy truffles
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes. Stir after each minute and stir until completely melted.
Beat cream cheese until smooth, gradually adding sugar.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then shape into 1-inch balls and roll in nuts or coconut.

title: angel pie
directions: Whip
cream and add sugar; set aside.
Stir lemon juice into condensed
milk,
add
pineapple and nuts.
Fold mixture into whipped
cream.
Pour
into pie shells; chill at least 2 hours before serving.
May be made the day before.

title: ranch veggies
directions: Combine Hidden Valley Original Ranch milk recipe dry salad dressing mix with oil in a large bowl.
Mix with frozen mixed vegetables and toss.
Bake in casserole dish in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes while baking.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; cut into small pieces.
In a saucepan, blend the butter, flour, water and soup.
Bring to a boil; stir constantly for 3 minutes.
Then add sour cream, chilies and mushrooms. Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Soften tortillas in hot oil and drain.
Roll chicken pieces in tortillas and arrange in a casserole dish.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken breast; save broth and set aside.
Chop peppers and onions, then simmer with butter.
Set aside.
Boil noodles and grate cheese.
Mix Ro-Tel, peas and mushrooms together.
Add onions, peppers, noodles and cheese to mixture with 1 cup chicken broth.
Put in pan and place chicken breast on top and bake until done.

title: beef steak pie
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch pieces and brown with the onions in the shortening.
Add the flour and blend, then add the water, carrots, celery, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add the potatoes and cook 15 minutes longer.
Pour into a casserole and cover with pie crust.
Place in hot oven (450°) and bake 30 minutes.

title: veal steaks in sour cream
directions: Using a large frying pan, saute the onion in about 1 1/2 tablespoons of the butter until golden.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Season veal steaks with salt and pepper.
Add the remaining butter to the frying pan and saute the veal over medium heat on both sides until tender and golden color.
Remove the meat and keep warm.
Reduce heat to low and add the onion to the pan; add sour cream and Gjetost.
Heat and stir until cheese melts. Return the meat to the pan and spoon the sauce over it; heat through.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Remove milk from freezer, open and set aside.
Beat 2 tablespoons milk into cream cheese; set aside.
Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups liquid.

title: delicious strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water (no cold); add other ingredients at once.
Let stand in refrigerator until real firm. Delicious!

title: moonshine sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites to a foam and add cream of tartar, then beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually to whites, then add beaten egg yolks and salt, then fold in flavoring and flour.
Bake in an angel food pan, greased and floured for 45 to 60 minutes at 300°.

title: mom's sauerkraut casserole
directions: Spread evenly half of well drained sauerkraut in a casserole pan.
In a separate bowl, mix ground meat, onions, rice, smoked ham and seasoning.
Spread mixture on top of sauerkraut in the casserole pan, then on top spread the remaining sauerkraut.
Pour the tomato juice on top of sauerkraut evenly, then sprinkle dill and thyme.
Cook in oven at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with sour cream.

title: orange tapioca dessert
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the first 3 ingredients, then cool. Add oranges and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease pan.
Cover bottom with chopped nuts.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and flavoring; mix well and put over nuts.
Sprinkle top with mixed fruit and top with coconut.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes or well browned.

title: coffee cake (not yeast)
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, nutmeg, salt and oil together.
Take out 3/4 cup.
To this, add cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
To the rest of the mixture, add the buttermilk, eggs and baking soda. Mix well and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nut mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar and water together; drizzle over warm cake.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Choose a cake mix and add eggs and vegetable oil.
Mix well.
You can add other ingredients like nuts, raisins or chocolate chips or any flavoring if you like. Drop teaspoonfuls of dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet, spacing about 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: golden delight punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except Mountain Dew.
Chill until serving time.
Add Mountain Dew prior to serving.
Make ice ring with juice mix frozen in jello mold.
Makes 50 (4 ounce) servings.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage and spread on bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Beat together milk, eggs and margarine.
Pour over sausage.
Over top of this, layer the hash browns and the Cheddar cheese.
Bake one hour.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Peel apples and chop.
Beat eggs, add oil and sugar.
Beat well by hand.
Gradually add flour to creamed mixture, then add vanilla.
Fold in chopped apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: hawaiian surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until firm.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, when dissolved add remaining ingredients and mix well. Place in greased bowl, Cover and refrigerate overnight or longer. Shape into rolls and place in greased pan. Makes 27-30 rolls. Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture.
Roll into balls.
Dip one side in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon. Bake on ungreased baking sheet (10 to 12 minutes) in 400° oven until slightly brown, but still soft.

title: creamed quail
directions: Salt and pepper quail.
Slowly simmer in butter in large heavy cast-iron pan (deep) until tender.
Add cream and simmer unti done, whisking to blend.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender.
Add sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
(Add additional milk if needed.)

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend with milk.
Drop by teaspoon on the bottom of ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a water glass bottom which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 12 minutes.
Yields about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: coconut swine cake
directions: Drain 2/3 cup pineapple juice for batter.
Bake cake as directed using juice instead of water using 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. While cake is hot, punch holes in it with fork and spread Eagle Brand milk on top.
Let cool completely.
Spread crushed pineapple and juice on top of cake.
Then spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in iron skillet at 450° until done (approximately 20 minutes).

title: old fashion tomato preserves
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a hard boil for two minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Process or cook; set on shelf.
This makes good meat loaf or Sloppy Joes mix.

title: four dozen cookies
directions: Divide dough into 4 parts; shape each roll 13-inches wide and 3/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 4 inches apart and 2 inches from edge of sheet.
Make a depression 1/4 to 1/3-inch deep, length of dough.
Fill with red jelly or jam, about 1/3 cup.
Bake until light brown and cut roll into 12 pieces.

title: cherry delight
directions: (Crust) Take the 1 1/2 cup graham cracker crumbs and 6 Tbsp. melted margarine; Press in a 9 x 12 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Coarsely grind fresh cranberries, orange and rind.
Add sugar; set overnight.
Add other ingredients and cool before adding to jello that has set slightly.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, cheese, sugar and bacon bits; let set until bacon bits soften.
Pour over raw broccoli, cauliflower and cabbage.
Better after it sits awhile.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and crabmeat.
Mix well.
Add each ingredient and stir.
Serve chilled with crackers or heat and serve with crackers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars with margarine.
Add oil and eggs.
Add vanilla. Combine dry ingredients and add.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt until shortening is in small pieces.
In a measuring cup, beat egg and add enough ice water to measure 2/3 cup.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Mix and roll into pie crusts.
This makes 5 or 6 crusts.
Stack and put into a freezer bag and freeze.
Use as needed.

title: flying saucer cookies
directions: Mix all.
Will be very stiff.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fat-free pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together the pumpkin, pumpkin pie spice, vanilla pudding and milk until smooth.
Add container of Cool Whip.
Pour in a graham cracker crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place into refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: gooseberry salad
directions: Add jello to boiling water.
Stir in marshmallow pieces. Chill until partially set.
Add gooseberries, nuts, celery and oranges.
Chill and cut in squares and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley flakes, bouillon cube and seasonings; mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until all veggies are tender.
Gradually add milk and flour mixture to vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: turkey legs
directions: One leg per person usually.
I use Corning Ware baking dish. Preheat oven to 325°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients until frozen juices are thawed and blended in.
Put into freezer to slush.

title: power cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and soda and beat into first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and knead together.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven about 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugars and vanilla; add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in peanut butter.
Stir dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Form into tiny balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Cook at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz, in casserole dish and cover with 1 cup Ritz (crushed).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: quick dip
directions: Beat ingredients together with electric mixer.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with chips, celery sticks and carrot sticks.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups water with spaghetti sauce in bowl.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups sauce. Arrange layer of uncooked noodles, slightly overlapping on top of sauce.
Spread half the Ricotta cheese and half the Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Repeat another layer of noodles, remaining Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of Parmesan.
Top with layer of noodles and pour remaining sauce over, spreading evenly to cover edges of noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan. Cover tightly with heavy-duty foil.
Set on jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until knife goes easily through pasta.
Let stand for 10 minutes on rack.

title: zingy cheese crackers
directions: Mix dry ingredients with crackers.
Pour oil over mixture, stirring until the oil is absorbed.
Add lemon pepper for extra zing!
Can be stored in tight container for 2 to 3 weeks, if they last that long!!

title: egg and pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, salt and vanilla and blend well. Stir in nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.
While hot, roll into additional powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten egg.
Combine 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with blueberries.
Blend remaining sugar, flour, cinnamon and 1/4 cup butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: party pink popcorn
directions: Make 2 quarts of popped popcorn (keep warm in oven).
In a saucepan, stir butter, marshmallows and jello until marshmallows are melted.
Pour mixture over popcorn and work in.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Boil beef shank in water.
Remove scum.
Add salt, bay leaves, peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Simmer until tomatoes flake (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Add celery, potatoes and carrots.
Boil 1/2 hour longer, then add beans, cabbage and macaroni.
Boil for 1/2 hour more.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and refrigerate for at least an hour.
Makes 2 servings.

title: nonfat yogurt
directions: Heat milk until warm.
Do not boil!
Stir in powdered milk and yogurt.
Pour into a suitable container and let stand in a warm place overnight (an oven with a pilot light is a good spot).
The next morning, refrigerate.
When this batch of yogurt is almost gone, save several spoonfuls for the next batch.
This will still work if the yogurt is frozen, then thawed for a new batch. Thickness can be changed by adding either more or less powdered milk.
You may also use regular or 2% milk.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in heavy 10-inch skillet or 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange pineapple on top of brown sugar and butter. Decorate with pecan halves and cherries, if desired.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixer bowl.
Add shortening, milk and flavorings.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add egg; beat 2 minutes more.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Immediately turn upside down onto serving plate.
Leave pan over cake a few minutes.
Brown sugar mixture will run down sides of cake.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: caramel delight
directions: Heat butter, pecans and coconut.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Layer the pecans and coconut mix, then the cream cheese mix, pecans and coconut mix, caramel topping, cream cheese mix, pecans and coconut mix and finally the caramel topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut tiny tops and stems from broccoli.
Mix onion and bacon with broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Marinate at least 2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix until well blended. Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mrs. eman's crumb cake
directions: Mix together flours, sugar, spices and margarine until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup of these crumbs and reserve for topping. Dissolve soda in milk or yogurt.
Add to mixture, stirring until blended.
Put batter into 2 greased 8-inch pans and top with crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and set aside.
Then mix together next four ingredients and set aside.
Beat together the next two ingredients.
In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, put a layer of stuffing mixture.
Top this with all of chicken, then top chicken with remaining stuffing mix.
Pour egg mix over top and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add cream of chicken soup on top of this and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream 1 stick butter with sugars (1 cup each brown and white) and mix with oatmeal.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread with topping.
Place cake under broiler until topping is bubbly and slightly browned.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool on racks.
Spread Raisin/Nut Filling between cooled layers.
Frost sides and top of cake with Southern Frosting.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Fry meat until brown.
Drain.
Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients except chips.
Put in ungreased baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle crushed chips over top.
Bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Carefully scoop cooked potato out of shell and into mixing bowl.
Add butter, milk and salt to taste; mash until lump-free.
Fill potato shells.
Top with cheese and place in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Boil together carrots, celery, onion, potatoes and basil. Cook until almost done.
In a separate, smaller pot, slowly cook milk, flour and cheese over medium heat until the cheese has melted and becomes sauce.
Stir the cheese sauce into the vegetable mix.
Add ham.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: back country venison
directions: Put everything in crock-pot and cook on low for 8 to 9 hours. The apples will almost cook away, leaving a thick gravy with very nice flavor to go with the venison.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple well; place in a casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour together; pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese over the entire casserole.
Then sprinkle crushed crackers over the top. Pour melted butter over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve while hot.
Great with ham.

title: tom thumbs
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, salt and flour.
Put in 9 x 11-inch pan and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Mix brown sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour, baking powder, salt, coconut and nuts. Spread over baked mixture.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes. Cut into bars when cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Chill dough for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Crush Oreo cookies and put in bottom of pan with melted butter.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk, then blend pudding and cream cheese together.
Pour over cookies.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Add soda to mashed bananas.
Mix all other ingredients; add to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Boil the water and butter.
Add flour and salt; stir until pulls away from side of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes at 400°.

title: hershey's brownies
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes in 8-inch square pan.

title: ann's sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into small bite size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(For best results mix small amounts at a time in blender until mixture is wet and pulpy.
These can be kept uncooked and frozen for about 3 weeks.
Add 10 minutes to baking time if frozen.)

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into uncooked pie shells; sprinkle top with finely chopped nuts.
Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: nut rolls
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and sugar as for pie dough.
Combine milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add to first mixture.
Also add yeast that has been dissolved in lukewarm water.
Work together for a few minutes until dough forms a ball.
Set aside for 2 1/2 hours to raise.
Divide into 4 pieces and roll on lightly floured board.
Spread with nut or apricot filling.
Bake immediately at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients in blender.
Hollow out rye bread to use as a bowl for dip.
Cut remaining bread into cubes for dipping.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease and flour a 10 x 4 Bundt pan. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, cream together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Gradually add flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan and bake for about 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.
Let cake cool about 20 minutes.
While cake is cooling prepare icing by bringing all remaining ingredients to a boil and boiling 2 minutes.
Pour over cake while icing is hot.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Grease pie pan (preferably glass).
Preheat oven to 325°. Combine egg and sugar in bowl.
Add flour; mix until mixture cleans sides of bowl (will be little thicker than muffin mix). Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie pan.
(It will spread out; don't you do it.)
It will spread itself in the oven. Bake for 35 minutes, or until top is crusty.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Mix in a saucepan sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in gradually the milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and gradually add at least 1/2 of hot mixture into egg yolks, then blend into hot mixture into saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue on top.

title: crunch slaw
directions: Crunch up noodles; toss with rest of slaw ingredients in a large bowl.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix together and simmer.

title: stained glass windows candy
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat; remove from heat. Add marshmallows and 1 cup nuts.
Shape into roll 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter; wrap in Reynolds Wrap and chill.
When rolls are thoroughly chilled, slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate maple nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 beaten egg. Press evenly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Place cauliflower and a small amount of water in a saucepan; cover and cook for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain. Combine cauliflower, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, cornflakes, peppers and salt; transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy pasta skillet
directions: Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Add 5 cups of water and bring to a boil; add pasta.
Cover and reduce heat to medium; simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and 2 cups of the
mozzarella cheese.
Before serving, add 1 cup mozzarella cheese and top with the parmesan cheese.

title: corn flake chews
directions: Boil sugar and syrup. Add butter, peanut butter and corn flakes. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: honey bun coffee cake
directions: Mix together and set aside the sugar, raisins and cinnamon. Mix together the cake mix, oil, sugar, eggs and sour cream. Divide batter between four 8-inch cake tins.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and raisins evenly over batter.
Gently swirl into batter with knife tip. Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes. Glaze while cake is hot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Dice stems and fry in margarine, along with the onion, pepperoni and garlic.
To that, add the crackers, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well, then add the broth and mix again.
Spoon this stuffing in mounds into the mushroom cavities, then place these mushroom caps (stuffed side up) in a baking pan with about 1/4-inch of water. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken dinner(serves 113)
directions: You will need 9 (9 x 13-inch) cakes.

title: crispy pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs; add shortening. Mix until smooth. Add flour to sugar mixture; blend until smooth. Beat on medium speed of electric mixer 10 to 15 minutes or until very fluffy. Beat at least 10 minutes. Spoon batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan. Spread coconut, pecans and chocolate chips over bottom. Mix together powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese. Drop by spoonfuls over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken roll-up
directions: Boil chicken and cut up into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken and sour cream and place on flattened biscuit.
Fold biscuit over and seal edges.
Place in baking dish and cover with soup and milk.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Steam chicken until cooked. Bone chicken and chop meat; set aside. Cook rice (instructions on box). Spoon cooked rice into lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Combine chicken and remaining ingredients except cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: sausage-squash casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Cook squash in small amount of water about 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 325° until firm and lightly browned (25 to 30 minutes).

title: pecan snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Roll into balls.
Dip in sugar and press pecan in center of each ball. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: have a good day soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Boil 10 minutes.
Makes 8 1/2 cups.
Serve with sandwiches and dessert.

title: bob's flaming rummed bananas
directions: Mix sugar and butter with enough milk to blend them thoroughly, then place in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Put bananas in casserole and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove and pour over them half of the rum and all of the sugar-butter-milk mixture, which has been reheated.
Return to oven for 5 minutes. Remove and pour remaining rum over the top. Light with a match as it is served.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon in bowl.
Add sugar and vinegar to salad dressing, mixing well.
Pour over salad, tossing to coat vegetables.
Chill until serving time.
Serves 8.

title: unbelievable pumpkin pie(dietetic)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch deep pie plate (I use a 9-inch round cake plate) with nonstick spray.
Beat all ingredients until smooth (1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes with hand mixer).
Pour into pie plate and bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar together.
Add pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Grate or crumb the cookies (works best if frozen).
Starting with crumbs, then alternate cream mixture, ending with cookie crumbs.
Put in flowerpot and just before serving, put in a pretty silk flower.
Serve with garden spade.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and butter together.
Knead until smooth and roll into tiny balls.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Using toothpick, dip balls in chocolate until half covered.
Set on foil covered tray.
Makes 75 to 100.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top and bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed, making 2 layers.
Cool.
Split in half, making 4 layers.
Mix together coconut, sugar and sour cream. Reserve 1 cup of this mixture.
Spread remainder between layers of cake along with a few tablespoons of the cream of coconut.
Mix 1 cup of reserved mixture with Cool Whip.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in Tupperware or tight cake keeper.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 days.

title: fruit tea
directions: Heat
tea
bags;
add sugar, orange juice and pineapple juice in pitcher.
Add cold water to make 1/2 gallon.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Toast top 2 ingredients at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; mix flour, baking powder and salt together. Add alternately with milk. Add vanilla and toasted pecans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter.
Remove from heat and stir in the sugar, corn syrup and oats.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture into the prepared crust.
Top with pecans.
Cover the edge with foil to prevent over browning.
Bake in a 325 oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes more or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Serve with whipped cream and top with baked pie crust shapes, if you like.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumbers scandinavian
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions; place in boil.
Add liquid and place in refrigerator.
Marinate and chill.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Bake pastry shell at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Combine cream cheese and milk in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Gradually add cream cheese mixture to eggs, mixing until well blended.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add onion and remaining ingredients to cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.

title: binky's pancit(from the philippines)
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil until soft.
Add celery, cabbage, carrot, beans and broth.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked.

title: cold veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on pizza pan and seal edges together forming a complete circle, bake according to package. Take out of oven and let cool.
In small bowl mix together cream cheese, dill weed and garlic powder.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crescent roll crust.
Spread chopped vegetables over cream cheese and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: daddy's apricot ice cream
directions: In a blender, mix sugar, apricots (including juice) and lemon juice.
Blend (if you want pieces of apricots, save some out and cut with a knife).
Put this mixture in the container for a one-gallon home freezer.
Ice it down and run (or crank) the freezer until it is well chilled.
Open container and add half and half, Carnation milk and vanilla.
Finish filling the container to the line with regular milk.
Freeze as you would any homemade ice cream.

title: just-my-size pizzas
directions: Turn the oven to 425°. Put some shortening on a piece of waxed paper or paper towel. Spread the shortening over the baking sheet.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Add soda to sour cream.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix to soft dough; let stand 5 minutes.
Roll out into rectangle shape.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold in half; cut into 1/2-inch wide strips and twist into braids.
Let rise for 1 hour or until doubled. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside. Beat egg whites and set aside. Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg yolks. Add vanilla and milk alternately with dry ingredients. Fold in beaten egg whites. Add blueberries. Pour in 9-inch square pan, greased and floured. Sprinkle batter with sugar for topping. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick chicken skillet
directions: Cut chicken into finger size strips.
In electric skillet at 350°, melt butter.
Add cut up chicken; cook for 3 minutes, turning constantly.
Add cut up green pepper, celery, salt, water and juice from pineapple.
Cover; cook for 3 minutes.
Add tarragon, onion flakes, chicken broth and pineapple chunks.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and cook for 4 minutes.
Add cold water to cornstarch to make a paste.
When 4 minutes cooking time is reached, add cornstarch gradually to thickness desired.
Add chopped pimento for color.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix in nuts and dates.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add liquid to flour mixture, stirring until flour is well moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean and beef barbecue bake
directions: Cook ground beef and vegetables until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Add tomato sauce, water, garlic, vinegar, mustard, thyme, parsley, cumin, brown sugar and seasoning.
Blend well and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour meat mixture over them.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Add cooked hamburg and onion.
Then add macaroni.
Put cheeses and pepperoni on top.
Put any extra goodies you would like on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bar-b-q pork roast and sauerkraut
directions: Cover tightly with lid or foil.
Cook 350° until meat is cooked.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Put meat and water in slow cooker and cook on low 8 to 10 hours. When done, it should shred easily with a fork. Remove from slow cooker and shred meat with 2 forks. Put back into slow cooker (make sure you discard the water and fat) or large casserole dish. Add sauce and serve with rice or on hamburger buns.

title: indian shrimp
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy saucepan and add the onions until they are golden brown.
Reduce the heat and add garlic, ginger and chili; saute an additional minute.
Add the turmeric and coriander and then the coconut milk and salt.
Cook the sauce until it thickens, approximately 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in the shrimp and simmer until the shrimp are cooked through (turn pink), approximately 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Stir in the fresh coriander and serve on puff pastry squares.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes (preferably on the grill).
Cut the potatoes in half and scoop out the insides.
Mash potatoes; add all ingredients (except paprika) and whip until smooth.
Make boats from foil; put the potato shell in the boats.
Fill with potato mixture.
Sprinkle paprika on the potatoes and return them to the oven for 15 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Stir mixture until it boils.
Continue to boil until done, about 10 minutes.
Cook 5 minutes more, add nuts, then beat until candy loses gloss.

title: chicken stew(serves 4)
directions: In 5-quart saucepan, heat oil.
In batches, add chicken and brown on all sides.
Set chicken aside.
In same pot, combine onions, celery and bell peppers; saute until onions are golden. Add tomatoes (with liquid) and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Return chicken to pot and stir to combine.
Reduce heat to low; cover and let simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix last 4 ingredients in a roaster. Add roast and coat with liquid. Cover well and bake for 5 hours, flipping roast halfway through. Remove roast. Use dripping for gravy.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and make onions into rings.
Boil potatoes and onion for 1 minute.
Put a layer of onions and potatoes in casserole dish.
Cover with sliced cheese, pats of butter, salt, pepper and half of mushroom soup, slightly diluted with milk.
Put other layer of onion and potatoes and repeat other ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: house of grace tea
directions: Mix in gallon jar.
Finish filling with water.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: tropical fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line two 9-inch round cake pans with foil.
Lightly grease foil.

title: kentucky corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Beat in eggs, then stir in corn and cream until blended.
Bake for 45 minutes or until slightly puffed and golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: baked rice custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in milk, cooked rice and raisins.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Let this set for 5 minutes before baking at 325° until set, 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water enough to cover.
Boil 3 minutes. Dissolve soda in cooled raisin water.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and mix well.
Add raisins, cooked oatmeal and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon and cloves; mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, cheese, margarine, sour cream, onion, soup, salt and pepper.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 cup margarine with cornflakes.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(May be prepared ahead of time and frozen.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 3/4-inch cubes and dredge with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until all ingredients are well blended. Cover skillet and cook until steaming.
Reduce heat to low and cook 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: church windows
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and butter.
Cool.
Add chopped nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with flaked coconut on wax paper.
Spoon mixture on coconut in log form.
Sprinkle coconut on top of log.
Wrap in the wax paper and refrigerate 2 or more hours.
Remove from refrigerator.
Slice and serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes.
(Put in icebox for a while and then dice.) Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat and add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until bubbly. Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Also add 2 tablespoons onions, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk if necessary.
Serve with remaining onions, cheese and bacon on top.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle cheese and chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to
8 servings.

title: chicken picante
directions: About 50 minutes before serving, in large bowl, mix sauce, mustard and lime juice.
Add chicken breasts, turning to coat. Cover, marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot butter or margarine, arrange chicken in one layer, reserving marinade.
Cook chicken until brown on both sides.
Add marinade and cook about 5 minutes longer until chicken is tender and marinade glazes the chicken.

title: casserole chicken
directions: Place chicken on rice in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix canned soups and milk together. Pour over rice before adding chicken. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 325° for 2 1/4 hours.
Do not peek.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll each piece of biscuit in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Put in a Bundt pan. Melt margarine.
Mix with the 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour mixture over biscuits and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: marinade for barbecuing
directions: Mix in glass or plastic container.
Place meat (beef or venison) in marinade overnight.
Cook meat on grill, basting with leftover marinade.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Braise chops; place in casserole.
Brown rice and place over chops.
Saute sliced onion, minced garlic and green pepper.
Place over rice.
Pour in tomatoes, consomme and Worcestershire sauce. Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding and milk in a mixing bowl. Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix with spoon.
Pour into a serving dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: fudge(super)
directions: Mix together the chocolate chips and margarine in microwave. Beat eggs and combine with sifted powdered sugar.
Add melted mixture and beat well.
Add nuts.
Use 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Blend all ingredients well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with more crushed crackers blended with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crackers are brown.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage, onion and ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Melt cheese.
Combine with meat and remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips.

title: patti's pizza
directions: Add yeast to 1/4 c. lukewarm water and set aside for 5 minutes. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt; make into a well. Add 1 c. warm water and olive oil.
Stir slightly, add yeast and stir well.
Turn onto floured surface and knead well.
Oil hands and form dough into a ball, making sure surface of dough is coated with oil.
Place ball in large greased bowl and cover with wax paper.
Cover with a tea towel.
Let rise 1 hour in a warm place.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine and mix until well blended.

title: apple loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into 2 large greased bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown the meat slowly. Spoon off excess fat.
Add the garlic, parsley flakes, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste to meat. Simmer, uncovered, until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake together thoroughly in a jar.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first nine ingredients; mix well.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with potato chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: spinach cheesy
directions: Mix cheese and eggs together and toss with spinach.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Add spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots for 8 minutes.
Heat vinegar, tomato soup and sugar.
Add onions, celery and/or green peppers.
Pour heated mixture over vegetables.
Chill.

title: meat pies
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add chopped onion and Velveeta cheese. Stir.
Let cool.
Put 1 tablespoon of meat onto each biscuit.
Fold biscuit over and seal with fork.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: oyster cracker snacks]
directions: Combine crackers, dill weed, dressing mix, garlic salt and Beau Monde in paper bag or large bowl.
Shake or stir.
Warm oil and pour over mixture.
Shake or stir again.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 10 cups.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Cover cabbage and onion rings with sugar.
Pour sauce over cabbage.
Refrigerate.
Do not stir until ready to serve.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well except bread crumbs.
Pour into large baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: youngberry cobbler
directions: Cream butter and 1/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and alternate with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into greased casserole.
Pour drained berries over batter and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Pour 1 cup berry juice over all.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: perfect brownies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in chocolate, vanilla and flour.
Mix in nuts.
Pour in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Frost if desired.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Combine all ingredients in a plastic bag.
Salt and pepper fish.
Rub fish with a little margarine and roll in dry ingredients mixture.
Bake fish in pan with rack at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Before putting fish on rack spray with Pam to prevent sticking.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla; beat at low speed until smooth.
Add rolled oats and raisins.
Blend or drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: slushy punch
directions: Stir 2 3/4 cups water and sugar together.
Blend bananas, half the pineapple juice and orange juice until smooth. Add to sugar mixture. Stir in remaining pineapple juice and lemon juice. Can also add 1 1/2 cups rum or vodka.
Freeze in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind all vegetables together.
Salt to taste.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 15 minutes.
Drain very well.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes. Put into jars and seal.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and crisco. Beat in well beaten eggs. Add buttermilk and soda. Add flour one cup at a time. Add baking powder. Stir in vanilla. Refrigerate over night. Flour table well. Place a small amount of dough on flour. Sprinkle flour on top and pat out with hand to 1/2 inch thick. Cut with floured cookie cutters. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: *Follow recipe on box, except use 1 extra egg and use milk instead of water.

title: creamy chicken broccoli fettucine
directions: Heat salad dressing in large skillet. Add chicken; cook and stir 8 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in broccoli and prepared cheese product.
Cook on low heat until prepared cheese product is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add hot fettucine; toss until well coated.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, butter and water.
Divide in half.
Parboil squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soup and sour cream to carrots.
Add the squash and onion.
Spread half the stuffing in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle the other half of the stuffing mix over this. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar together.
Cut in butter and mix well.
Press into thin crust in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: onion blossom
directions: Cut onion in quarters, then in eighths so it will open like a flower.
Place in boiling water for 1 minute, then into ice water 5 minutes; drain.
Place onion in Ziploc bag with flour; then dip into beaten egg.
Put back into bag with cracker crumbs and chill for 1 hour.
Pour oil 3 inches deep and heat to 375°.
Fry 5 to 7 minutes and drain on paper towel.
Serve with Ranch dip with horseradish or any other vegetable dip.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line buttered casserole dish with chips.
Add layer of chicken.
Combine chilies, sauteed onion, soups and milk.
Pour over chicken. Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mattie's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salt water until tender; drain. Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french green beans
directions: Cover beans with water.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until done. Drain.
Melt margarine in skillet; cook and stir onions in margarine over medium heat until golden.
Add green beans and pepper.
Cook and stir until beans begin to brown.
Turn into warm serving dish.
Sprinkle with vinegar, lemon juice and parsley; toss.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine celery, soup and evaporated milk.
Add macaroni, salmon and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Turn into greased casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese around edge. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Blend vinegar, mayonnaise and mustard in a bowl.
Add sugar, onion, honey and parsley.
Season to taste.
Mix well. Whisk in oil gradually.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain liquid from 1 jar of artichokes into 1-quart saucepan. Drain liquid from second jar of artichokes and discard.
Finely chop all artichokes; set aside.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Mix well.
Marinate any red meat overnight; best flavor if grilled.

title: chinese new year rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok.
Stir-fry chicken.
Add vegetables to stir-fry.
Add soy sauce and rice and cook until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: mountaineer salad
directions: Grate cabbage.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and peanuts.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix well - Yummy!

title: quick caramel popcorn
directions: Pour popcorn into brown paper grocery sack.
Bring to a boil the butter, sugar and Karo or honey; then add baking soda.
(It will puff up.)
Pour over popcorn; shake well.
Microwave for 1/2 minute; shake well.
Pour on wax paper.
Let cool and eat!

title: barbecue short ribs
directions: Dredge ribs in flour.
Lay ribs in large casserole or pan. Combine all ingredients, except onion.
Lay onion over ribs.
Pour sauce over.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: christmas cider
directions: Pour cider into saucepan and heat on stove.
Put large cinnamon stick in bottom of the saucepan.
As your guests arrive pour into cups and add one candy cane and about a tablespoon of whipped cream.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in butter, flour, sugar, coconut and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie crust and bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until filling sets.

title: shellfish stew
directions: Cook bacon; then add
onion and green pepper.
Continue cooking until light brown.
Add tomatoes and 1 1/2 cups water. Add potatoes, salt, garlic,
oregano
and
pepper.
Simmer
20 minutes or until potatoes
are
tender.
Add veggies and mushrooms;
cook about 10
minutes.
Put
in
shrimp,
oysters and clams.
Bring to a boil and cook another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Boil round slices of potatoes until almost done.
Line bottom of casserole dish with ground beef.
Put layer of potatoes on ground beef, then a layer of tomatoes. Do this until all ingredients are used.
Pour juice from the tomatoes over all. Put lid on casserole and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Heat butter and olive oil in medium saucepan or skillet.
Add garlic.
Cook 1 minute. Stir in flour until absorbed.
Stir in juice from chopped clams.
Stir in white cooking wine, parsley, thyme and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Add reserved clams and cook until heated through.
Serve over linguini.
Serves 2.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute the 3 kinds of meat with onions, celery, green peppers and garlic.
Add crumbled corn bread.
Stuff the bell peppers; pour tomato sauce over them.
Bake!

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and corn flakes.
Place in a 2-quart greased casserole.
Pour butter over top.
Sprinkle corn flakes over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna-lemon loaf
directions: Place lemon slices, in a row, in the bottom of a very well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Thoroughly combine remaining ingredients except egg whites; fold in egg whites.
Spoon tuna mixture over lemon slices in loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center of loaf is firm. Invert on warm serving platter.
Garnish with parsley and additional lemon slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jelly roll
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt; beat for 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Spread in a jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until cake "sizzles."
Place a clean cloth dish towel which has been dusted with powdered sugar over pan when it comes from the oven.
Invert pan, spread with jelly of your choice.
Roll carefully and allow to cool.
Dust with sifted powdered sugar and serve.

title: plum coffee cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add food coloring and strained plums.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 325°.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: light fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic, saute 1 minute.
Stri in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended; cook 8 minutes or until thickened stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese, cook 2 minutes.

title: eleanor's fudgies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts. Beat together thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 12-inch or 11 x 17-inch pan.
Batter will be thin.
Spread evenly into pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over batter and nuts, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares or bars.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix together cornmeal, flour and sugar in shallow bowl. Dredge both sides of tomatoes in mixture.
Press slices firmly into meal to coat thoroughly.
Pour about 1/4 inch oil in cast-iron skillet and heat.
Add tomatoes a few at a time without crowding and fry about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pound cake(two flours)
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco with electric mixer on medium speed. Let eggs reach room temperature.
Add eggs one at a time, creaming well.
Add vanilla, milk and flour.
Blend about 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in tube pan and bake 1 hour at 325° or until golden brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Note: One can mixed vegetables may be used instead of the boiled eggs.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Unroll crescent rolls to form squares.
Pat any holes together.
Spread with cream cheese, then top with sausage.
Roll up and seal edge together.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to cook, slice each roll into 10 pinwheels. If frozen, let warm up a little before slicing.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 375°
about 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and let cool. Add 1/2 cup juice from frozen strawberries. Combine other ingredients. Blend together for 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 layers.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Drop dough by tablespoons 3-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes; cool.
Cut off tops and fill with creamed tuna for luncheon or ice cream with chocolate topping or cream pie filling for dessert.
Makes 6 puffs.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar and salt with corn meal and blend well.
Add butter and pour in 1 1/3 cups boiling water, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool.
Beat eggs with baking powder until very light and fluffy, then add to corn meal mixture.
Stir in milk and pour into prepared casserole. Place casserole in shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening until light and fluffy.
Then cream sugar in. Mix in well beaten eggs.
Mash bananas.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake in long loaf pan 40 to 50 minutes at 325° or until toothpick comes out clean when you test it.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine yeast and sugar with warm milk.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix with flour, baking powder and shortening.
Knead and pinch off small pieces, forming a roll.
Place on cookie sheet or round pan.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole dish first.
Add orange juice, water, bouillon cubes and pork chops.
Melt bouillon cubes in water.
Fry pork chops just a little brown.
Place chops on top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: maple butternut pie
directions: Mix ingredients just enough to blend.
Add broken butternuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 350° but turn down to 325° when you put the pie in the oven.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until just set in the center.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: chicken imperial ala taffine
directions: On waxed paper, coat chicken breasts with 1/4 cup flour.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter or margarine, cook chicken, a few pieces at a time until lightly browned on all sides.
Set chicken breasts aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix equal parts of the ingredients and chill.

title: lovers' wedding cake
directions: Put love, good looks and sweet temper into a well-furnished home.
Mix buttered youth together with a blindness of faults and self-forgetfulness.
Throw in dry humor and sweet arguments.
Then add to the above.
Pour in gently, rippling laughter and common sense.
Then bake gently forever.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese. Stir in pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt. Chill. Form into ball and roll in remaining chopped pecans. Makes 1 large or 2 small balls. Freezes well.

title: clams and beer
directions: In a large stockpot combine beer, oil and garlic.
Place clams in pot.
Cover and steam approximately 10 minutes or until clams open.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a crock-pot which has been greased well.
Cut several thin slices of cheese and put on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook for 3 hours on low.

title: quick chicken shortcake
directions: Remove	biscuits
from	package.
Flatten biscuits with hand to	make
circles
about
3-inches	in diameter.
Place 5 biscuits on	baking	sheet; brush with a little melted butter. Top each biscuit with another biscuit.
Press edges together. Bake in very hot
oven
for
to 8 minutes or until browned.

title: hot holiday punch
directions: Place juices, water, sugar and salt in a percolator coffeepot. Place cloves and cinnamon sticks in the basket of the pot.
Plug up and perk.
Serves 30.

title: smoked sausage and rice dish
directions: Heat butter in electric frypan.
Add peppers and sliced sausages.
Stir-fry for a few minutes until sausage browns a little, then add tomatoes that have been cut up.
Add salt, pepper and rice; bring to a boil, then lower heat and cover and simmer 15 or 20 minutes.

title: seafood delight salad
directions: Chop crabmeat, olives, celery and onions. Cook pasta and cool. Mix all ingredients together. Add salad dressing to your liking.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Spread thinly with spatula on large (approximately 12 x 17-inch) ungreased cookie sheet (with 1/2-inch sides).
Brush top with unbeaten egg white.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares or diamond shapes.
Remove immediately.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate and milk chocolate in separate containers.
Add the peanut butter to the white chocolate.
